<div class="page" data-ng-controller="HtmlCtrl" >
  <div class="constitute-html csection">
    <h1 class="clearfix">
    Burkina Faso 1991 (rev. 2012)
    
    
  
    
  
    
</h1>


<p class="copyright">English Translation Â© 2012 by William S. Hein &amp; Co., Inc.  All rights reserved.</p>


<p class="translator">Translated by Jefri J. Ruchti</p>

  <div class="constitution-content" data-languages="en">
<div class="constitution-topics"></div>
<div class="constitution-content__copy"><!--Section: section/0, type: -->
<div id="s0" data-link-target="s0" data-id="section/0" class="section"><!--Section: section/1, type: title-->
<div id="s1" data-link-target="s1" data-id="section/1" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="preamble">Preamble</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="auth">Source of constitutional authority</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="motive">Motives for writing constitution</span>
</div>
<h2 class="upper depth-0">Preamble</h2><!--Section: section/2, type: body-->
<div id="s2" data-link-target="s2" data-id="section/2" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">We, the Sovereign People of Burkina Faso:</p><!--Section: section/3, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s3" data-link-target="s3" data-id="section/3">CONSCIOUS of our responsibilities and of our duties before history and before humanity;<!--Section: section/5, type: body-->
<div id="s5" data-link-target="s5" data-id="section/5" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">STRENGTHENED by the democracies [we have] acquired;</p></div><!--Section: section/6, type: body-->
<div id="s6" data-link-target="s6" data-id="section/6" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="dignity">Human dignity</span>
</div><p class="content">COMMITTED to preserve those acquired and animated by a will to construct a State of law guaranteeing the exercise of collective and individual rights, liberty, dignity, security, well-being, development, equality and justice as the fundamental values of a pluralist society of progress and free from all prejudice;</p></div><!--Section: section/7, type: body-->
<div id="s7" data-link-target="s7" data-id="section/7" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">REAFFIRMING our commitment to the struggle against any form of domination as well as to the democratic character of power;</p></div><!--Section: section/8, type: body-->
<div id="s8" data-link-target="s8" data-id="section/8" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">DETERMINED to promote integrity, probity, transparence, impartiality and the obligation to render account as the republican and ethical values proper to moralize the life of the Nation;</p></div><!--Section: section/9, type: body-->
<div id="s9" data-link-target="s9" data-id="section/9" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">RECOGNIZING the customary and traditional leadership as [a] moral authority[,] depository of the customs and of the traditions in our society;</p></div><!--Section: section/10, type: body-->
<div id="s10" data-link-target="s10" data-id="section/10" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">RECOGNIZING that the promotion of gender is a factor for realization of the equality of law between men and women of Burkina Faso;</p></div><!--Section: section/11, type: body-->
<div id="s11" data-link-target="s11" data-id="section/11" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="region">Regional group(s)</span>
</div><p class="content">SEARCHING [for] the economic and political integration with the other peoples of Africa with a view to the construction of a federative unity of Africa;</p></div><!--Section: section/12, type: body-->
<div id="s12" data-link-target="s12" data-id="section/12" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intrght">International human rights treaties</span>
</div><p class="content">SUBSCRIBING to the Universal Declaration of the Rights of Man of 1948 and to the international instruments concerning economic, political, social and cultural problems;</p></div><!--Section: section/13, type: body-->
<div id="s13" data-link-target="s13" data-id="section/13" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intrght">International human rights treaties</span>
</div><p class="content">REAFFIRMING solemnly our commitment vis-a-vis the African Charter of the Rights of Man and of Peoples of 1981;</p></div><!--Section: section/14, type: body-->
<div id="s14" data-link-target="s14" data-id="section/14" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">DESIROUS to promote peace, international cooperation, the peaceful resolution of differences between States, with justice, equality, liberty and the sovereignty of peoples;</p></div><!--Section: section/15, type: body-->
<div id="s15" data-link-target="s15" data-id="section/15" class="section article-list level1 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>
</div><p class="content">CONSCIOUS of the absolute necessity to protect the environment;</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/16, type: body-->
<div id="s16" data-link-target="s16" data-id="section/16" class="section article-list level1 article-body"><p class="content">APPROVE and ADOPT this Constitution of which this preamble is made an integral part.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/17, type: title-->
<div id="s17" data-link-target="s17" data-id="section/17" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE I. OF THE FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS AND DUTIES</h3><!--Section: section/18, type: title-->
<div id="s18" data-link-target="s18" data-id="section/18" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">CHAPTER I. OF CIVIL RIGHTS AND DUTIES</h3><!--Section: section/19, type: title-->
<div id="s19" data-link-target="s19" data-id="section/19" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 1</h3><!--Section: section/20, type: body-->
<div id="s20" data-link-target="s20" data-id="section/20" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="equal">General guarantee of equality</span>
</div><p class="content">All the Burkinabe are born free and equal in rights.</p></div><!--Section: section/21, type: body-->
<div id="s21" data-link-target="s21" data-id="section/21" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">All have an equal vocation to enjoy all the rights and all the freedoms guaranteed by this Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/22, type: body-->
<div id="s22" data-link-target="s22" data-id="section/22" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr5">Equality regardless of language</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr4">Equality regardless of race</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr6">Equality regardless of religion</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr10">Equality regardless of skin color</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr1">Equality regardless of gender</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr15">Equality regardless of political party</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="equalgr13">Equality regardless of financial status</span>
</div><p class="content">Discrimination of all sorts, notably those founded on race, ethnicity, region, color, sex, language, religion, caste, political opinions, wealth and birth, are prohibited.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/23, type: title-->
<div id="s23" data-link-target="s23" data-id="section/23" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 2</h3><!--Section: section/24, type: body-->
<div id="s24" data-link-target="s24" data-id="section/24" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="life">Right to life</span>
</div><p class="content">The protection of life, security, and physical integrity are guaranteed.</p></div><!--Section: section/25, type: body-->
<div id="s25" data-link-target="s25" data-id="section/25" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="torture">Prohibition of torture</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cruelty">Prohibition of cruel treatment</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="slave">Prohibition of slavery</span>
</div><p class="content">Slavery, slavery-like practices, inhuman and cruel, degrading and humiliating treatments, physical or moral torture, services and mistreatments inflicted on children and all forms of the degradation of Man[,] are forbidden and punished by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/26, type: title-->
<div id="s26" data-link-target="s26" data-id="section/26" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="habcorp">Protection from unjustified restraint</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 3</h3><!--Section: section/27, type: body-->
<div id="s27" data-link-target="s27" data-id="section/27" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">No one may be deprived of his liberty if he is not prosecuted for acts specified and punishable by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/28, type: body-->
<div id="s28" data-link-target="s28" data-id="section/28" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="citdep">Power to deport citizens</span>
</div><p class="content">No one may only be arrested, detained, deported or exiled by virtue of the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/29, type: title-->
<div id="s29" data-link-target="s29" data-id="section/29" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="fairtri">Right to fair trial</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 4</h3><!--Section: section/30, type: body-->
<div id="s30" data-link-target="s30" data-id="section/30" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">All Burkinabe and all persons living in Burkina Faso benefit from an equal protection of the law. All have the right to have their case heard by an independent and impartial jurisdiction.</p></div><!--Section: section/31, type: body-->
<div id="s31" data-link-target="s31" data-id="section/31" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="presinoc">Presumption of innocence in trials</span>
</div><p class="content">Any accused is presumed innocent until his guilt has been established.</p></div><!--Section: section/32, type: body-->
<div id="s32" data-link-target="s32" data-id="section/32" class="section article-list level3 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="couns">Right to counsel</span>
</div><p class="content">The right to a defense, including that of freely choosing one&#x27;s defender is guaranteed before all the jurisdictions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/33, type: title-->
<div id="s33" data-link-target="s33" data-id="section/33" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="wolaw">Principle of no punishment without law</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="expost">Protection from ex post facto laws</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 5</h3><!--Section: section/34, type: body-->
<div id="s34" data-link-target="s34" data-id="section/34" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Anything which is not forbidden by the law may not be hindered and no one can be constrained to do that which [the law] does not order.</p></div><!--Section: section/35, type: body-->
<div id="s35" data-link-target="s35" data-id="section/35" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The penal law does not have retroactive effect. One may only be judged and punished by virtue of a law promulgated and published prior to the punishable act.</p></div><!--Section: section/36, type: body-->
<div id="s36" data-link-target="s36" data-id="section/36" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Punishment is personal and individual.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/37, type: title-->
<div id="s37" data-link-target="s37" data-id="section/37" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="inalrght">Inalienable rights</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="privacy">Right to privacy</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 6</h3><!--Section: section/38, type: body-->
<div id="s38" data-link-target="s38" data-id="section/38" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The residence, the domicile, private and family life, [and] the secrecy of correspondence of every person, are inviolable.</p></div><!--Section: section/39, type: body-->
<div id="s39" data-link-target="s39" data-id="section/39" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">It can only be infringed according to the forms and in the cases specified by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/40, type: title-->
<div id="s40" data-link-target="s40" data-id="section/40" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="assem">Freedom of assembly</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="freerel">Freedom of religion</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 7</h3><!--Section: section/41, type: body-->
<div id="s41" data-link-target="s41" data-id="section/41" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The freedom of belief, of non-belief, of conscience, of religious opinion, [of] philosophy, of exercise of belief, the freedom of assembly, the free practice of custom as well as the freedom of procession and of demonstration, are guaranteed by this Constitution, under reserve of respect for the law, for public order, for good morals and for the human person.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/42, type: title-->
<div id="s42" data-link-target="s42" data-id="section/42" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="opinion">Freedom of opinion/thought/conscience</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="press">Freedom of press</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="express">Freedom of expression</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="infoacc">Right to information</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 8</h3><!--Section: section/43, type: body-->
<div id="s43" data-link-target="s43" data-id="section/43" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The freedoms of opinion, of the press and the right to information are guaranteed.</p></div><!--Section: section/44, type: body-->
<div id="s44" data-link-target="s44" data-id="section/44" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every person has the right to express and to disseminate his opinions within the order of the laws and regulations in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/45, type: title-->
<div id="s45" data-link-target="s45" data-id="section/45" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="asylum">Protection of stateless persons</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="freemove">Freedom of movement</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 9</h3><!--Section: section/46, type: body-->
<div id="s46" data-link-target="s46" data-id="section/46" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The free circulation of persons and of assets, the free choice of residence and the right of asylum, are guaranteed within the order of the laws and regulations in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/47, type: title-->
<div id="s47" data-link-target="s47" data-id="section/47" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="milserv">Duty to serve in the military</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 10</h3><!--Section: section/48, type: body-->
<div id="s48" data-link-target="s48" data-id="section/48" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every Burkinabe citizen has the duty to participate in the defense and in the maintenance of the territorial integrity.</p></div><!--Section: section/49, type: body-->
<div id="s49" data-link-target="s49" data-id="section/49" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">He is required to fulfill national service when it is required of him.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/50, type: title-->
<div id="s50" data-link-target="s50" data-id="section/50" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">CHAPTER II. OF POLITICAL RIGHTS AND DUTIES</h3><!--Section: section/51, type: title-->
<div id="s51" data-link-target="s51" data-id="section/51" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 11</h3><!--Section: section/52, type: body-->
<div id="s52" data-link-target="s52" data-id="section/52" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">All Burkinabe enjoy civil and political rights within the conditions specified by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/53, type: title-->
<div id="s53" data-link-target="s53" data-id="section/53" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 12</h3><!--Section: section/54, type: body-->
<div id="s54" data-link-target="s54" data-id="section/54" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">All the Burkinabe without any distinction, have the right to participate in the conduct of the affairs of the State and of society.</p></div><!--Section: section/55, type: body-->
<div id="s55" data-link-target="s55" data-id="section/55" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">In this capacity, they are electors and eligible within the conditions specified by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/56, type: title-->
<div id="s56" data-link-target="s56" data-id="section/56" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="partprh">Prohibited political parties</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="partrght">Right to form political parties</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 13</h3><!--Section: section/57, type: body-->
<div id="s57" data-link-target="s57" data-id="section/57" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The political parties and formations create themselves freely.</p></div><!--Section: section/58, type: body-->
<div id="s58" data-link-target="s58" data-id="section/58" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">They participate in the activity of political life, in the information and the education of the people as well as in the expression of suffrage.</p></div><!--Section: section/59, type: body-->
<div id="s59" data-link-target="s59" data-id="section/59" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">They conduct their activities freely within respect for the laws.</p></div><!--Section: section/60, type: body-->
<div id="s60" data-link-target="s60" data-id="section/60" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">All the political parties or formations are equal in rights and in duties.</p></div><!--Section: section/61, type: body-->
<div id="s61" data-link-target="s61" data-id="section/61" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">However, tribalist, regionalist, denominational, or racist political parties or formations are not authorized.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/62, type: title-->
<div id="s62" data-link-target="s62" data-id="section/62" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">CHAPTER III. OF ECONOMIC RIGHTS AND DUTIES</h3><!--Section: section/63, type: title-->
<div id="s63" data-link-target="s63" data-id="section/63" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="resrce">Ownership of natural resources</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 14</h3><!--Section: section/64, type: body-->
<div id="s64" data-link-target="s64" data-id="section/64" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The natural wealth and resources belong to the people.</p></div><!--Section: section/65, type: body-->
<div id="s65" data-link-target="s65" data-id="section/65" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">They are utilized for the amelioration of their conditions of life.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/66, type: title-->
<div id="s66" data-link-target="s66" data-id="section/66" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="exprop">Protection from expropriation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="proprght">Right to own property</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 15</h3><!--Section: section/67, type: body-->
<div id="s67" data-link-target="s67" data-id="section/67" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right of property is guaranteed. It may not be exercised contrary to social utility or in a manner which results in prejudice to the security, to liberty, to existence or to the property of others.</p></div><!--Section: section/68, type: body-->
<div id="s68" data-link-target="s68" data-id="section/68" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">It can only be infringed the in case of public necessity declared in the legal forms.</p></div><!--Section: section/69, type: body-->
<div id="s69" data-link-target="s69" data-id="section/69" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">No one will be deprived of their possessions if it is not for [a] cause of public utility and under the condition of a just indemnity established conforming to the law. This indemnity must be prior to the expropriation, except in case of urgency or of force majeure.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/70, type: title-->
<div id="s70" data-link-target="s70" data-id="section/70" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="busines">Right to establish a business</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 16</h3><!--Section: section/71, type: body-->
<div id="s71" data-link-target="s71" data-id="section/71" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The freedom of enterprise is guaranteed within the order of the laws and regulations in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/72, type: title-->
<div id="s72" data-link-target="s72" data-id="section/72" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 17</h3><!--Section: section/73, type: body-->
<div id="s73" data-link-target="s73" data-id="section/73" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The duty to fulfill one&#x27;s fiscal obligations conforming to the law is imposed on each one.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/74, type: title-->
<div id="s74" data-link-target="s74" data-id="section/74" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">CHAPTER IV. OF SOCIAL AND CULTURAL RIGHTS AND DUTIES</h3><!--Section: section/75, type: title-->
<div id="s75" data-link-target="s75" data-id="section/75" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="finsup1">State support for the elderly</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="shelter">Right to shelter</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="leisure">Right to rest and leisure</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="science">Reference to science</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="finsup3">State support for the disabled</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cultrght">Right to culture</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="artists">Reference to art</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 18</h3><!--Section: section/76, type: body-->
<div id="s76" data-link-target="s76" data-id="section/76" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Education, instruction, [professional] training, work, social security, housing, sport, leisure, health, protection of Maternity and of Infancy, assistance to the aged or handicapped persons and [those] in social cases, [and] artistic and scientific creation, constitute the social and cultural rights recognized by this Constitution which sees to their promotion.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/77, type: title-->
<div id="s77" data-link-target="s77" data-id="section/77" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="provwork">Right to work</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="remuner">Right to just remuneration</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 19</h3><!--Section: section/78, type: body-->
<div id="s78" data-link-target="s78" data-id="section/78" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right to work is recognized and is equal for all.</p></div><!--Section: section/79, type: body-->
<div id="s79" data-link-target="s79" data-id="section/79" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">It is prohibited to discriminate in matters of employment and of remuneration founded notably on sex, color, social origin, ethnicity or political opinion.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/80, type: title-->
<div id="s80" data-link-target="s80" data-id="section/80" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 20</h3><!--Section: section/81, type: body-->
<div id="s81" data-link-target="s81" data-id="section/81" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The State sees to the constant amelioration of the conditions of work and to the protection of the worker.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/82, type: title-->
<div id="s82" data-link-target="s82" data-id="section/82" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="assoc">Freedom of association</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="jointrde">Right to join trade unions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 21</h3><!--Section: section/83, type: body-->
<div id="s83" data-link-target="s83" data-id="section/83" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The freedom of association is guaranteed. Every person has the right to constitute associations and to participate freely in the activities of the associations created. The functioning of the associations must conform to the laws and regulations in force.</p></div><!--Section: section/84, type: body-->
<div id="s84" data-link-target="s84" data-id="section/84" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The syndical freedom is guaranteed. The unions exercise their activities without constraint and without limitation other than those specified by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/85, type: title-->
<div id="s85" data-link-target="s85" data-id="section/85" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="strike">Right to strike</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 22</h3><!--Section: section/86, type: body-->
<div id="s86" data-link-target="s86" data-id="section/86" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right to strike is guaranteed. It is exercised conforming to the laws in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/87, type: title-->
<div id="s87" data-link-target="s87" data-id="section/87" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="marriage">Regulation of marriage</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="matequal">Provision for matrimonial equality</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 23</h3><!--Section: section/88, type: body-->
<div id="s88" data-link-target="s88" data-id="section/88" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The family is the basic unit of society. The State has the duty to protect it.</p></div><!--Section: section/89, type: body-->
<div id="s89" data-link-target="s89" data-id="section/89" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Marriage is founded on the free consent of the man and of the woman. All discrimination based on race, color, religion, ethnicity, caste, social origin, [and] fortune, is forbidden in matters of marriage.</p></div><!--Section: section/90, type: body-->
<div id="s90" data-link-target="s90" data-id="section/90" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Children are equal in rights and in duties in their familial relations. The parents have the natural right and the duty to raise and to educate their children. These must give them respect and assistance.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/91, type: title-->
<div id="s91" data-link-target="s91" data-id="section/91" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="childpro">Rights of children</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 24</h3><!--Section: section/92, type: body-->
<div id="s92" data-link-target="s92" data-id="section/92" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The State works to promote the rights of the child.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/93, type: title-->
<div id="s93" data-link-target="s93" data-id="section/93" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="transfer">Right to transfer property</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 25</h3><!--Section: section/94, type: body-->
<div id="s94" data-link-target="s94" data-id="section/94" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right to transmit oneâs assets by inheritance or gift is recognized conforming to the laws and regulations in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/95, type: title-->
<div id="s95" data-link-target="s95" data-id="section/95" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="health">Right to health care</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 26</h3><!--Section: section/96, type: body-->
<div id="s96" data-link-target="s96" data-id="section/96" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right to health is recognized. The State works to promote it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/97, type: title-->
<div id="s97" data-link-target="s97" data-id="section/97" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 27</h3><!--Section: section/98, type: body-->
<div id="s98" data-link-target="s98" data-id="section/98" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every citizen has the right to instruction.</p></div><!--Section: section/99, type: body-->
<div id="s99" data-link-target="s99" data-id="section/99" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Public education is secular.</p></div><!--Section: section/100, type: body-->
<div id="s100" data-link-target="s100" data-id="section/100" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Private education is recognized. The law establishes the conditions of its exercise.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/101, type: title-->
<div id="s101" data-link-target="s101" data-id="section/101" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intprop">Provisions for intellectual property</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="science">Reference to science</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="artists">Reference to art</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 28</h3><!--Section: section/102, type: body-->
<div id="s102" data-link-target="s102" data-id="section/102" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The law guarantees intellectual property.</p></div><!--Section: section/103, type: body-->
<div id="s103" data-link-target="s103" data-id="section/103" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The freedom of creation and [of] artistic, scientific and technical works, are protected by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/104, type: body-->
<div id="s104" data-link-target="s104" data-id="section/104" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The manifestation of cultural, intellectual, artistic and scientific activity is free and is exercised conforming to the texts in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/105, type: title-->
<div id="s105" data-link-target="s105" data-id="section/105" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 29</h3><!--Section: section/106, type: body-->
<div id="s106" data-link-target="s106" data-id="section/106" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">The right to a healthy environment is recognized; the protection, the defense and the promotion of the environment are a duty for all.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/107, type: title-->
<div id="s107" data-link-target="s107" data-id="section/107" class="section article-list level2 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="petition">Right of petition</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-2">Article 30</h3><!--Section: section/108, type: body-->
<div id="s108" data-link-target="s108" data-id="section/108" class="section article-list level3 article-body"><p class="content">Every citizen has the right to initiate an action or participate in a collective action under the form of petition against the acts:</p><!--Section: section/109, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s109" data-link-target="s109" data-id="section/109">harming the public patrimony;<!--Section: section/111, type: body-->
<div id="s111" data-link-target="s111" data-id="section/111" class="section article-list level3 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">harming the interests of the social communities;</p></div><!--Section: section/112, type: body-->
<div id="s112" data-link-target="s112" data-id="section/112" class="section article-list level3 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>
</div><p class="content">infringing the environment or the cultural or historic patrimony.</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/113, type: title-->
<div id="s113" data-link-target="s113" data-id="section/113" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE II. OF THE STATE AND OF NATIONAL SOVEREIGNTY</h3><!--Section: section/114, type: title-->
<div id="s114" data-link-target="s114" data-id="section/114" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="system">Type of government envisioned</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="seprel">Separation of church and state</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="offrel">Official religion</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 31</h3><!--Section: section/115, type: body-->
<div id="s115" data-link-target="s115" data-id="section/115" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Burkina Faso is a democratic, unitary and secular State.</p></div><!--Section: section/116, type: body-->
<div id="s116" data-link-target="s116" data-id="section/116" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Faso is the republican form of the State.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/117, type: title-->
<div id="s117" data-link-target="s117" data-id="section/117" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 32</h3><!--Section: section/118, type: body-->
<div id="s118" data-link-target="s118" data-id="section/118" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">National sovereignty belongs to the people who exercise it under the conditions specified by this Constitution and by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/119, type: title-->
<div id="s119" data-link-target="s119" data-id="section/119" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freeelec">Secret ballot</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="voteun">Claim of universal suffrage</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 33</h3><!--Section: section/120, type: body-->
<div id="s120" data-link-target="s120" data-id="section/120" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Suffrage is direct or indirect and exercised under the conditions specified by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/121, type: body-->
<div id="s121" data-link-target="s121" data-id="section/121" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Direct suffrage is always universal, equal and secret.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/122, type: title-->
<div id="s122" data-link-target="s122" data-id="section/122" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="anthem">National anthem</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="flag">National flag</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="motto">National motto</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 34</h3><!--Section: section/123, type: body-->
<div id="s123" data-link-target="s123" data-id="section/123" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The symbols of the Nation are constituted by an emblem, by a coat-of-arms, by an anthem and by a motto.</p></div><!--Section: section/124, type: body-->
<div id="s124" data-link-target="s124" data-id="section/124" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The emblem is the tri-colored flag of rectangular and horizontal form, red and green with, in its center, a yellow-gold star of five points.</p><!--Section: section/125, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s125" data-link-target="s125" data-id="section/125">The law determines the coat-of-arms as well as the signification of its constituent elements.<!--Section: section/127, type: body-->
<div id="s127" data-link-target="s127" data-id="section/127" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">The national anthem is the DITANYE.</p></div><!--Section: section/128, type: body-->
<div id="s128" data-link-target="s128" data-id="section/128" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">The motto is: UNITE - PROGRES - JUSTICE [Unity - Progress - Justice].</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div><!--Section: section/129, type: title-->
<div id="s129" data-link-target="s129" data-id="section/129" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="lang">Official or national languages</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="langprot">Protection of language use</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 35</h3><!--Section: section/130, type: body-->
<div id="s130" data-link-target="s130" data-id="section/130" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The official language is French.</p></div><!--Section: section/131, type: body-->
<div id="s131" data-link-target="s131" data-id="section/131" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes the modalities of the promotion and of the official use of the national languages.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/132, type: title-->
<div id="s132" data-link-target="s132" data-id="section/132" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE III. OF THE PRESIDENT OF FASO</h3><!--Section: section/133, type: title-->
<div id="s133" data-link-target="s133" data-id="section/133" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="execnum">Name/structure of executive(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 36</h3><!--Section: section/134, type: body-->
<div id="s134" data-link-target="s134" data-id="section/134" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is the Head of the State.</p></div><!--Section: section/135, type: body-->
<div id="s135" data-link-target="s135" data-id="section/135" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He sees to the respect of the Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/136, type: body-->
<div id="s136" data-link-target="s136" data-id="section/136" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He establishes the principal orientations of the policy of the State.</p></div><!--Section: section/137, type: body-->
<div id="s137" data-link-target="s137" data-id="section/137" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He incarnates and assures the national unity.</p></div><!--Section: section/138, type: body-->
<div id="s138" data-link-target="s138" data-id="section/138" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He is the guarantor of the national independence, of the integrity of the territory, of the permanence and of the continuity of the State, [and] of respect for agreements and treaties.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/139, type: title-->
<div id="s139" data-link-target="s139" data-id="section/139" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="freeelec">Secret ballot</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosterml">Head of state term limits</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosterm">Head of state term length</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hoselect">Head of state selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="voteun">Claim of universal suffrage</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 37</h3><!--Section: section/140, type: body-->
<div id="s140" data-link-target="s140" data-id="section/140" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is elected for five years by universal, direct, equal and secret suffrage. He is re-eligible one time.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/141, type: title-->
<div id="s141" data-link-target="s141" data-id="section/141" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosage">Minimum age of head of state</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosrest">Eligibility for head of state</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 38</h3><!--Section: section/142, type: body-->
<div id="s142" data-link-target="s142" data-id="section/142" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every candidate to the functions of President of Faso must be Burkinabe by birth, be thirty-five years of age at least and of seventy-five years [of age] at most at the date of deposit of his candidature[,] and meeting the conditions required by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/143, type: title-->
<div id="s143" data-link-target="s143" data-id="section/143" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hoselect">Head of state selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 39</h3><!--Section: section/144, type: body-->
<div id="s144" data-link-target="s144" data-id="section/144" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is elected by the absolute majority of the suffrage expressed.</p></div><!--Section: section/145, type: body-->
<div id="s145" data-link-target="s145" data-id="section/145" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If this majority is not obtained in the first round of the ballot, it proceeds fifteen (15) days later to a second round. Only the two candidates can present themselves who, as the case may be, after withdrawal of the less favored candidates, are found to have received the greatest number of votes at the first round; the President of Faso is then elected by simple majority.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/146, type: title-->
<div id="s146" data-link-target="s146" data-id="section/146" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 40</h3><!--Section: section/147, type: body-->
<div id="s147" data-link-target="s147" data-id="section/147" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The elections are set twenty-one days at least and forty days at most before the expiration of the mandate of the President in office.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/148, type: title-->
<div id="s148" data-link-target="s148" data-id="section/148" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 41</h3><!--Section: section/149, type: body-->
<div id="s149" data-link-target="s149" data-id="section/149" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law determines the procedure, the conditions of eligibility and of presentation of the candidatures to the presidential elections, of the conduct of the ballot, of the counting and of the proclamation of the results. It specifies all the provisions required so that the elections will be free, honest and regular.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/150, type: title-->
<div id="s150" data-link-target="s150" data-id="section/150" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 42</h3><!--Section: section/151, type: body-->
<div id="s151" data-link-target="s151" data-id="section/151" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The functions of the President of Faso are incompatible with the exercise of all other elective mandate of national level, of any public employment and of any professional activity.</p></div><!--Section: section/152, type: body-->
<div id="s152" data-link-target="s152" data-id="section/152" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The provisions of Articles 72, 73, 74 and 75 of this Constitution are applicable to the President of Faso.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/153, type: title-->
<div id="s153" data-link-target="s153" data-id="section/153" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hossucc">Head of state replacement</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 43</h3><!--Section: section/154, type: body-->
<div id="s154" data-link-target="s154" data-id="section/154" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">While the President of Faso is incapacitated in a temporary manner from fulfilling his functions, his powers are provisionally exercised by the Prime Minister.</p></div><!--Section: section/155, type: body-->
<div id="s155" data-link-target="s155" data-id="section/155" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In case of vacancy of the Presidency of Faso for any cause that may be, or of absolute or definitive incapacity declared by the Constitutional Council referred to [the matter] by the Government, the functions of the President of Faso are exercised by the President of the Senate. It proceeds to the election of a new President for a new period of five years.</p></div><!--Section: section/156, type: body-->
<div id="s156" data-link-target="s156" data-id="section/156" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The election of the new President takes place sixty days at least and ninety days at most after [the] official declaration of the vacancy or of the definitive character of the incapacity.</p></div><!--Section: section/157, type: body-->
<div id="s157" data-link-target="s157" data-id="section/157" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Senate exercising the functions of the President of Faso may not be [a] candidate at this presidential election.</p></div><!--Section: section/158, type: body-->
<div id="s158" data-link-target="s158" data-id="section/158" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In all cases, application may not be made of Articles 46, 49, 50, 59, and 161 of this Constitution during the vacancy of the Presidency.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/159, type: title-->
<div id="s159" data-link-target="s159" data-id="section/159" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="oath">Oaths to abide by constitution</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 44</h3><!--Section: section/160, type: body-->
<div id="s160" data-link-target="s160" data-id="section/160" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Before entering into [his] functions, the President elected swears before the Constitutional Council the following oath: &quot;I swear before the Burkinabe people and on my honor to preserve, to respect, to have respected and to defend the Constitution and the laws, and to implement it to guarantee justice to all the inhabitants of Burkina Faso.&quot;</p></div><!--Section: section/161, type: body-->
<div id="s161" data-link-target="s161" data-id="section/161" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In the course of the ceremony of investiture, the President of the Constitutional Council receives the written declaration of the assets of the President of Faso.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/162, type: title-->
<div id="s162" data-link-target="s162" data-id="section/162" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 45</h3><!--Section: section/163, type: body-->
<div id="s163" data-link-target="s163" data-id="section/163" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes the civil list of service to the President of Faso. It organizes the service of a pension in favor of former Presidents.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/164, type: title-->
<div id="s164" data-link-target="s164" data-id="section/164" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabsel">Cabinet selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogelect">Head of government selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 46</h3><!--Section: section/165, type: body-->
<div id="s165" data-link-target="s165" data-id="section/165" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso appoints the Prime Minister from among the majority of the National Assembly and terminates his functions, either on the presentation by him of his resignation, or on his own authority in the superior interest of the Nation.</p></div><!--Section: section/166, type: body-->
<div id="s166" data-link-target="s166" data-id="section/166" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">On the proposal of the Prime Minister, he appoints the other members of the Government and terminates their functions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/167, type: title-->
<div id="s167" data-link-target="s167" data-id="section/167" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 47</h3><!--Section: section/168, type: body-->
<div id="s168" data-link-target="s168" data-id="section/168" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso presides over the Council of Ministers. The Prime Minister substitutes for him with the conditions established by this Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/169, type: title-->
<div id="s169" data-link-target="s169" data-id="section/169" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="override">Veto override procedure</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legapp">Approval or veto of general legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 48</h3><!--Section: section/170, type: body-->
<div id="s170" data-link-target="s170" data-id="section/170" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso promulgates the law within the twenty-one days which follow the transmission of the text definitively adopted. This time period is reduced to eight days in case of urgency declared by the National Assembly or the Senate.</p></div><!--Section: section/171, type: body-->
<div id="s171" data-link-target="s171" data-id="section/171" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso can, during the time period of promulgation, demand a second reading of the law or of certain of its articles; the demand may not be refused. This procedure suspends the time periods of promulgation.</p></div><!--Section: section/172, type: body-->
<div id="s172" data-link-target="s172" data-id="section/172" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In default of promulgation within the time periods required, the law enters automatically into force following [the] declaration of the Constitutional Council.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/173, type: title-->
<div id="s173" data-link-target="s173" data-id="section/173" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="referen">Referenda</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 49</h3><!--Section: section/174, type: body-->
<div id="s174" data-link-target="s174" data-id="section/174" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso can, after [the] opinion of the Prime Minister, of the President of the Senate and of the President of the National Assembly, submit to referendum any bill of the law concerning any question of national interest.</p></div><!--Section: section/175, type: body-->
<div id="s175" data-link-target="s175" data-id="section/175" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In [the] case of the adoption of the said law, it proceeds to its promulgation in the time periods specified in Article 48.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/176, type: title-->
<div id="s176" data-link-target="s176" data-id="section/176" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legdiss">Dismissal of the legislature</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 50</h3><!--Section: section/177, type: body-->
<div id="s177" data-link-target="s177" data-id="section/177" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso can, after consultation of the Prime Minister, of the President of the Senate and of the President of the National Assembly, declare the dissolution of the National Assembly. In [the] case of dissolution, the legislative elections take place sixty days at least and ninety days at most after the dissolution.</p></div><!--Section: section/178, type: body-->
<div id="s178" data-link-target="s178" data-id="section/178" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It may not proceed to a new dissolution in the year which follows these elections.</p></div><!--Section: section/179, type: body-->
<div id="s179" data-link-target="s179" data-id="section/179" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The dissolved National Assembly may not meet.</p></div><!--Section: section/180, type: body-->
<div id="s180" data-link-target="s180" data-id="section/180" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, the mandate of the Deputies only expires at the date of validation of the mandate of the members of the new National Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/181, type: title-->
<div id="s181" data-link-target="s181" data-id="section/181" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 51</h3><!--Section: section/182, type: body-->
<div id="s182" data-link-target="s182" data-id="section/182" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso communicates with the two Chambers of the Parliament, either in person, or by the messages which he has read by the President of each Chamber and which do not give rise to any debate. Out of session, the Chambers of the Parliament meet specially to this effect.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/183, type: title-->
<div id="s183" data-link-target="s183" data-id="section/183" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="comchief">Designation of commander in chief</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 52</h3><!--Section: section/184, type: body-->
<div id="s184" data-link-target="s184" data-id="section/184" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is the Supreme Head of the National Armed Forces; in this capacity, he presides over the Superior Council of Defense.</p></div><!--Section: section/185, type: body-->
<div id="s185" data-link-target="s185" data-id="section/185" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He appoints the Major General Head of State of the Armies.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/186, type: title-->
<div id="s186" data-link-target="s186" data-id="section/186" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 53</h3><!--Section: section/187, type: body-->
<div id="s187" data-link-target="s187" data-id="section/187" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is the President of the Superior Council of the Magistrature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/188, type: title-->
<div id="s188" data-link-target="s188" data-id="section/188" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="pardon">Power to pardon</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 54</h3><!--Section: section/189, type: body-->
<div id="s189" data-link-target="s189" data-id="section/189" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso exercises the right of pardon. He proposes the laws of amnesty.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/190, type: title-->
<div id="s190" data-link-target="s190" data-id="section/190" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hospow">Head of state powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="headforn">Foreign affairs representative</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="intorgs">International organizations</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="milcom">Selection of active-duty commanders</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 55</h3><!--Section: section/191, type: body-->
<div id="s191" data-link-target="s191" data-id="section/191" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso appoints to the offices of the high civil and military administration[,] as well as in the societies and enterprises of strategic character determined by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/192, type: body-->
<div id="s192" data-link-target="s192" data-id="section/192" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He appoints the ambassadors and the extraordinary envoys to the foreign powers and to international organizations.</p></div><!--Section: section/193, type: body-->
<div id="s193" data-link-target="s193" data-id="section/193" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The foreign ambassadors and extraordinary envoys are accredited to him.</p></div><!--Section: section/194, type: body-->
<div id="s194" data-link-target="s194" data-id="section/194" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He appoints the Grand Chancellor of the Order Burkinabe.</p></div><!--Section: section/195, type: body-->
<div id="s195" data-link-target="s195" data-id="section/195" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A law determines the functions or offices for which the power of appointment of the President of Faso is exercised after [the] opinion of the Parliament as well as the modalities and effects of this consultation.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/196, type: title-->
<div id="s196" data-link-target="s196" data-id="section/196" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 56</h3><!--Section: section/197, type: body-->
<div id="s197" data-link-target="s197" data-id="section/197" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law determines the other offices which he provides for in the Council of Ministers, as well as the conditions in which the powers of appointment of the President are exercised.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/198, type: title-->
<div id="s198" data-link-target="s198" data-id="section/198" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 57</h3><!--Section: section/199, type: body-->
<div id="s199" data-link-target="s199" data-id="section/199" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Acts of the President of Faso other than those specified in Articles 46, 49, 50, 54 and 59 are countersigned by the Prime Minister, as the case may be, by the concerned Ministers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/200, type: title-->
<div id="s200" data-link-target="s200" data-id="section/200" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 58</h3><!--Section: section/201, type: body-->
<div id="s201" data-link-target="s201" data-id="section/201" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso decrees, after deliberation in the Council of Ministers, the state of siege and the state of urgency.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/202, type: title-->
<div id="s202" data-link-target="s202" data-id="section/202" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 59</h3><!--Section: section/203, type: body-->
<div id="s203" data-link-target="s203" data-id="section/203" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">When the Institutions of Faso, the independence of the Nation, the integrity of its territory or the execution of its obligations are menaced in a grave and immediate manner and/or that the regular functioning of the public constitutional powers is interrupted, the President of Faso takes, after deliberation in the Council of Ministers, after official consultation of the Presidents of the Senate, of the National Assembly and of the Constitutional Council, the measures required by the circumstances. He informs the Nation of it by a message. In no case, may he make an appeal to foreign armed forces to intervene in an internal conflict. The Parliament meets of plain right and the National Assembly may not be dissolved during the exercise of exceptional powers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/204, type: title-->
<div id="s204" data-link-target="s204" data-id="section/204" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 60</h3><!--Section: section/205, type: body-->
<div id="s205" data-link-target="s205" data-id="section/205" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso can delegate certain of his powers to the Prime Minister.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/206, type: title-->
<div id="s206" data-link-target="s206" data-id="section/206" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE IV. OF THE GOVERNMENT</h3><!--Section: section/207, type: title-->
<div id="s207" data-link-target="s207" data-id="section/207" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 61</h3><!--Section: section/208, type: body-->
<div id="s208" data-link-target="s208" data-id="section/208" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Government is an organ of the Executive.</p></div><!--Section: section/209, type: body-->
<div id="s209" data-link-target="s209" data-id="section/209" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It conducts the policy of the Nation; in this capacity, it is obligatorily referred to [matters]:</p><!--Section: section/210, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s210" data-link-target="s210" data-id="section/210">of drafts of international agreements;<!--Section: section/212, type: body-->
<div id="s212" data-link-target="s212" data-id="section/212" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of bills and proposals of law;</p></div><!--Section: section/213, type: body-->
<div id="s213" data-link-target="s213" data-id="section/213" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of drafts of regulatory texts.</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/214, type: body-->
<div id="s214" data-link-target="s214" data-id="section/214" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It [has at its] disposal the administration and the forces of defense and of security.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/215, type: title-->
<div id="s215" data-link-target="s215" data-id="section/215" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabinet">Establishment of cabinet/ministers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 62</h3><!--Section: section/216, type: body-->
<div id="s216" data-link-target="s216" data-id="section/216" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Government is responsible before the Parliament in the conditions and following the procedures specified by this Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/217, type: title-->
<div id="s217" data-link-target="s217" data-id="section/217" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogsucc">Head of government replacement</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogpow">Head of government powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="execnum">Name/structure of executive(s)</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogelect">Head of government selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 63</h3><!--Section: section/218, type: body-->
<div id="s218" data-link-target="s218" data-id="section/218" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister is the Head of the Government; in this capacity, he directs and coordinates the governmental action.</p></div><!--Section: section/219, type: body-->
<div id="s219" data-link-target="s219" data-id="section/219" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He is responsible for the implementation of the policy of national defense defined by the President of Faso.</p></div><!--Section: section/220, type: body-->
<div id="s220" data-link-target="s220" data-id="section/220" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He exercises the regulatory power conforming to the law, assures the implementation of the laws, appoints to civil and military offices other than those relevant to the competence of the President of Faso.</p></div><!--Section: section/221, type: body-->
<div id="s221" data-link-target="s221" data-id="section/221" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In the thirty days which follow his appointment, the Prime Minister makes a declaration of general policy before the National Assembly.</p></div><!--Section: section/222, type: body-->
<div id="s222" data-link-target="s222" data-id="section/222" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This declaration is followed by debates and gives rise to a vote.</p></div><!--Section: section/223, type: body-->
<div id="s223" data-link-target="s223" data-id="section/223" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The adoption of this declaration validates investiture.</p></div><!--Section: section/224, type: body-->
<div id="s224" data-link-target="s224" data-id="section/224" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the declaration of general policy does not receive the absolute majority of the members composing the National Assembly, the President of Faso terminates the functions of the Prime Minister within a time of eight days.</p></div><!--Section: section/225, type: body-->
<div id="s225" data-link-target="s225" data-id="section/225" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He appoints a new Prime Minister in accordance with the provisions of Article 46 above.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/226, type: title-->
<div id="s226" data-link-target="s226" data-id="section/226" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 64</h3><!--Section: section/227, type: body-->
<div id="s227" data-link-target="s227" data-id="section/227" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister assures the presidency of the Council of Ministers by delegation and for a specific agenda.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/228, type: title-->
<div id="s228" data-link-target="s228" data-id="section/228" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 65</h3><!--Section: section/229, type: body-->
<div id="s229" data-link-target="s229" data-id="section/229" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister determines the attributions of the members of the Government. These attributions are established by decree taken in the Council of Ministers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/230, type: title-->
<div id="s230" data-link-target="s230" data-id="section/230" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 66</h3><!--Section: section/231, type: body-->
<div id="s231" data-link-target="s231" data-id="section/231" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The acts of the Prime Minister are, as the case may be, countersigned by the members of the Government responsible for their implementation.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/232, type: title-->
<div id="s232" data-link-target="s232" data-id="section/232" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 67</h3><!--Section: section/233, type: body-->
<div id="s233" data-link-target="s233" data-id="section/233" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister can delegate certain of his powers to members of the Government.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/234, type: title-->
<div id="s234" data-link-target="s234" data-id="section/234" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 68</h3><!--Section: section/235, type: body-->
<div id="s235" data-link-target="s235" data-id="section/235" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the Government are responsible for the management of their respective departments before the Prime Minister. They are jointly responsible for the decisions of the Council of Ministers.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/236, type: title-->
<div id="s236" data-link-target="s236" data-id="section/236" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 69</h3><!--Section: section/237, type: body-->
<div id="s237" data-link-target="s237" data-id="section/237" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Any vacancy of the post of Prime Minister automatically terminates the functions of the other members of the Government. In this case, the latter expedite the current affairs until the formation of a new Government.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/238, type: title-->
<div id="s238" data-link-target="s238" data-id="section/238" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hoglegr">Head of government's role in the legislature</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 70</h3><!--Section: section/239, type: body-->
<div id="s239" data-link-target="s239" data-id="section/239" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The functions of a member of the Government are incompatible with the exercise of any parliamentary mandate, of any remunerated professional activity and of any function of professional representation.</p></div><!--Section: section/240, type: body-->
<div id="s240" data-link-target="s240" data-id="section/240" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, the exercise of functions of professional representation of international character is possible with the prior agreement of the Government.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/241, type: title-->
<div id="s241" data-link-target="s241" data-id="section/241" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 71</h3><!--Section: section/242, type: body-->
<div id="s242" data-link-target="s242" data-id="section/242" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every person appointed to exercise ministerial functions obligatorily benefits from a leave of absence or from a suspension of contract of work[,] according to the case.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/243, type: title-->
<div id="s243" data-link-target="s243" data-id="section/243" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 72</h3><!--Section: section/244, type: body-->
<div id="s244" data-link-target="s244" data-id="section/244" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the Government must not expose themselves to any situation susceptible of creating conflicts between the duties of their functions and their private interests.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/245, type: title-->
<div id="s245" data-link-target="s245" data-id="section/245" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 73</h3><!--Section: section/246, type: body-->
<div id="s246" data-link-target="s246" data-id="section/246" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">During the term of their functions, the members of the Government may not directly or indirectly buy or lease anything which belongs to the domain of the State. The law will specify the cases where this provision can be derogated.</p></div><!--Section: section/247, type: body-->
<div id="s247" data-link-target="s247" data-id="section/247" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">They may not take part in sales and in adjudications held by the Administration or by the Institutions corresponding to the State or submitted to its control.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/248, type: title-->
<div id="s248" data-link-target="s248" data-id="section/248" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 74</h3><!--Section: section/249, type: body-->
<div id="s249" data-link-target="s249" data-id="section/249" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">No member of Government may make a profit through his position, or make use of[,] directly or indirectly for personal ends[,] information that is communicated to him.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/250, type: title-->
<div id="s250" data-link-target="s250" data-id="section/250" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 75</h3><!--Section: section/251, type: body-->
<div id="s251" data-link-target="s251" data-id="section/251" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The provisions of Article 73 remain applicable for members of the Government during the six months which follow the cessation of their functions.</p></div><!--Section: section/252, type: body-->
<div id="s252" data-link-target="s252" data-id="section/252" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Those of Article 74 remain applicable during the two years which follow the cessation of their functions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/253, type: title-->
<div id="s253" data-link-target="s253" data-id="section/253" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabdiss">Cabinet removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 76</h3><!--Section: section/254, type: body-->
<div id="s254" data-link-target="s254" data-id="section/254" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Each member of the Government is responsible before the High Court of Justice for the crimes and misdemeanors committed by him during the exercise of his functions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/255, type: title-->
<div id="s255" data-link-target="s255" data-id="section/255" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabrest">Eligibility for cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 77</h3><!--Section: section/256, type: body-->
<div id="s256" data-link-target="s256" data-id="section/256" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">On their entry into their functions and to the end of their exercise, the members of the Government are required to provide a list of their assets to the Constitutional Council.</p></div><!--Section: section/257, type: body-->
<div id="s257" data-link-target="s257" data-id="section/257" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This obligation extends to all the Presidents of the institutions consecrated by the Constitution, as well as to other persons of distinction [concerning] which the list is determined by the law.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/258, type: title-->
<div id="s258" data-link-target="s258" data-id="section/258" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE V. OF THE PARLIAMENT</h3><!--Section: section/259, type: title-->
<div id="s259" data-link-target="s259" data-id="section/259" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="housenum">Structure of legislative chamber(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 78</h3><!--Section: section/260, type: body-->
<div id="s260" data-link-target="s260" data-id="section/260" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament consists of two Chambers: the National Assembly and the Senate.</p></div><!--Section: section/261, type: body-->
<div id="s261" data-link-target="s261" data-id="section/261" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Congress is the meeting of the two Chambers of the Parliament.</p></div><!--Section: section/262, type: body-->
<div id="s262" data-link-target="s262" data-id="section/262" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Congress meets under the presidency of the President of the National Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/263, type: title-->
<div id="s263" data-link-target="s263" data-id="section/263" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 79</h3><!--Section: section/264, type: body-->
<div id="s264" data-link-target="s264" data-id="section/264" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the National Assembly have the title of &quot;Deputy&quot; and those of the Senate, the title of &quot;Senator&quot;.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/265, type: title-->
<div id="s265" data-link-target="s265" data-id="section/265" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uhrest">Eligibility for second chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uhselect">Second chamber selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 80</h3><!--Section: section/266, type: body-->
<div id="s266" data-link-target="s266" data-id="section/266" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Senate is composed of representatives of the territorial collectivities, of the customary and religious authorities, of the employers, of the workers, of the Burkinabe living abroad and of persons of distinction appointed by the President of Faso.</p></div><!--Section: section/267, type: body-->
<div id="s267" data-link-target="s267" data-id="section/267" class="section article-list level2 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="voteun">Claim of universal suffrage</span>
</div><p class="content">The Senators representing the local collectivities are elected by those locally elected of their respective regions by universal indirect suffrage.</p></div><!--Section: section/268, type: body-->
<div id="s268" data-link-target="s268" data-id="section/268" class="section article-list level2 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uhage">Minimum age for second chamber</span>
</div><p class="content">The Senators representing the customary and religious authorities, the workers, the employers and the Burkinabe abroad are designated by their respective structures. No one may be elected or appointed Senator if they are not forty-five years old on the day of the ballot or of the appointment.</p></div><!--Section: section/269, type: body-->
<div id="s269" data-link-target="s269" data-id="section/269" class="section article-list level2 article-body">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="voteun">Claim of universal suffrage</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="freeelec">Secret ballot</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhselect">First chamber selection</span>
</div><p class="content">The Deputies are elected by direct, equal and secret universal suffrage.</p></div><!--Section: section/270, type: body-->
<div id="s270" data-link-target="s270" data-id="section/270" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every parliamentarian must benefit[,] the case arising, from a leave of absence or from a suspension of contract[,] as the case may be.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/271, type: title-->
<div id="s271" data-link-target="s271" data-id="section/271" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uhterm">Term length of second chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhterm">Term length for first chamber</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 81</h3><!--Section: section/272, type: body-->
<div id="s272" data-link-target="s272" data-id="section/272" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The duration of the mandate is of five (5) years for the Deputies and of six (6) years for the Senators.</p></div><!--Section: section/273, type: body-->
<div id="s273" data-link-target="s273" data-id="section/273" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, by derogation of the paragraph above and in the case of force majeure or of necessity expressed by the Government and recognized by the Parliament with the absolute majority of the votes of the members composing the Parliament, the duration of the legislature may be prorogued until the validation of the mandate of the Deputies or of the Senators of the new legislature.</p></div><!--Section: section/274, type: body-->
<div id="s274" data-link-target="s274" data-id="section/274" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This extension may not surpass a time of one (1) year.</p></div><!--Section: section/275, type: body-->
<div id="s275" data-link-target="s275" data-id="section/275" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This modification is applied to the current legislature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/276, type: title-->
<div id="s276" data-link-target="s276" data-id="section/276" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="district">Electoral districts</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhrest">Eligibility for first chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="profleg">Outside professions of legislators</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhage">Minimum age for first chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legrep">Replacement of legislators</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uhrest">Eligibility for second chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhselect">First chamber selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 82</h3><!--Section: section/277, type: body-->
<div id="s277" data-link-target="s277" data-id="section/277" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law determines:</p><!--Section: section/278, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s278" data-link-target="s278" data-id="section/278">the electoral circumscriptions;<!--Section: section/280, type: body-->
<div id="s280" data-link-target="s280" data-id="section/280" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the number of seats and their division;</p></div><!--Section: section/281, type: body-->
<div id="s281" data-link-target="s281" data-id="section/281" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the modes of the ballot;</p></div><!--Section: section/282, type: body-->
<div id="s282" data-link-target="s282" data-id="section/282" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the conditions of election, of designation and of replacement by new elections  or appointment in the case of vacancy of [a] seat, as well as the regime of the ineligibilities and of the incompatibilities;</p></div><!--Section: section/283, type: body-->
<div id="s283" data-link-target="s283" data-id="section/283" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="income">Compensation of legislators</span>
</div><p class="content">the status of the parliamentarians and the amount of their indemnities.</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div><!--Section: section/284, type: title-->
<div id="s284" data-link-target="s284" data-id="section/284" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 83</h3><!--Section: section/285, type: body-->
<div id="s285" data-link-target="s285" data-id="section/285" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It may not proceed to partial elections in the last third of the legislature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/286, type: title-->
<div id="s286" data-link-target="s286" data-id="section/286" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 84</h3><!--Section: section/287, type: body-->
<div id="s287" data-link-target="s287" data-id="section/287" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament votes the law, consents to taxation and controls the action of the Government conforming to the provisions of this Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/288, type: title-->
<div id="s288" data-link-target="s288" data-id="section/288" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legrep">Replacement of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 85</h3><!--Section: section/289, type: body-->
<div id="s289" data-link-target="s289" data-id="section/289" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Any imperative mandate is null.</p></div><!--Section: section/290, type: body-->
<div id="s290" data-link-target="s290" data-id="section/290" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, any Deputy who freely resigns from his party or from his political formation in the course of [a] legislature is replaced[,] of right[,] by a substitute. The law specifies the modalities of implementation of this provision.</p></div><!--Section: section/291, type: body-->
<div id="s291" data-link-target="s291" data-id="section/291" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">All the members of the Parliament have deliberative voice. The right to vote of the parliamentarians is personal. However the delegation of the vote is permitted when the absence of a member of the Parliament is justified. No one may validly receive for a given ballot more than one delegation of the vote.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/292, type: title-->
<div id="s292" data-link-target="s292" data-id="section/292" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 86</h3><!--Section: section/293, type: body-->
<div id="s293" data-link-target="s293" data-id="section/293" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every new Chamber of the Parliament proclaims the validity of the election or of the appointment of its members[,] notwithstanding the control of regularity exercised by the Constitutional Council.</p></div><!--Section: section/294, type: body-->
<div id="s294" data-link-target="s294" data-id="section/294" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It establishes its regulations.</p></div><!--Section: section/295, type: body-->
<div id="s295" data-link-target="s295" data-id="section/295" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the regulations concerning the organization and the functioning of the Chambers of the Parliament.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/296, type: title-->
<div id="s296" data-link-target="s296" data-id="section/296" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="session">Length of legislative sessions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 87</h3><!--Section: section/297, type: body-->
<div id="s297" data-link-target="s297" data-id="section/297" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Each Chamber of the Parliament meets of plain right each year in two ordinary sessions. The term of each may not exceed ninety days. The first session opens the first Wednesday of March and the second the last Wednesday of September. If the first Wednesday of March or the last Wednesday of September is a holiday, the session opens the first working day possible which follows.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/298, type: title-->
<div id="s298" data-link-target="s298" data-id="section/298" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="exsess">Extraordinary legislative sessions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 88</h3><!--Section: section/299, type: body-->
<div id="s299" data-link-target="s299" data-id="section/299" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Each Chamber of the Parliament meets in extraordinary session on convocation of its President[,] at the demand of the Prime Minister or of that of an absolute majority of the Deputies or of the Senators on a specific agenda. The extraordinary session is closed on completion of the agenda.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/300, type: title-->
<div id="s300" data-link-target="s300" data-id="section/300" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="pubmeet">Public or private sessions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 89</h3><!--Section: section/301, type: body-->
<div id="s301" data-link-target="s301" data-id="section/301" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The sittings of the Chambers of the Parliament are public. However they may be held in closed [session] in case of need.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/302, type: title-->
<div id="s302" data-link-target="s302" data-id="section/302" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 90</h3><!--Section: section/303, type: body-->
<div id="s303" data-link-target="s303" data-id="section/303" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Except [in the] case of force majeure declared by the Constitutional Council, the deliberations of each Chamber of the Parliament are valid only if they have taken place at its seat.</p></div><!--Section: section/304, type: body-->
<div id="s304" data-link-target="s304" data-id="section/304" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The deliberations of the Congress may be made in any other place regularly determined by joint decision of the President of the National Assembly and of the President of the Senate.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/305, type: title-->
<div id="s305" data-link-target="s305" data-id="section/305" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="stdcom">Standing committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhlead">Leader of first chamber</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uhlead">Leader of second chamber</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 91</h3><!--Section: section/306, type: body-->
<div id="s306" data-link-target="s306" data-id="section/306" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of the Senate and the President of the National Assembly are elected for the duration of the legislature by the absolute majority in the first round, or by the simple majority at the second round.</p></div><!--Section: section/307, type: body-->
<div id="s307" data-link-target="s307" data-id="section/307" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the Bureau are elected for one year, renewable.</p></div><!--Section: section/308, type: body-->
<div id="s308" data-link-target="s308" data-id="section/308" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, their functions can be terminated during the course of the legislature at the demand of two-fifths[,] and after a vote of the absolute majority[,] of the members of the Assembly.</p></div><!--Section: section/309, type: body-->
<div id="s309" data-link-target="s309" data-id="section/309" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">By absolute majority [it] is understood [to mean] more than half of the votes.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/310, type: title-->
<div id="s310" data-link-target="s310" data-id="section/310" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 92</h3><!--Section: section/311, type: body-->
<div id="s311" data-link-target="s311" data-id="section/311" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In case of vacancy of the presidency of a Chamber of the Parliament by death, resignation or for any other cause, the said Chamber elects a new President within the conditions defined in Article 91.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/312, type: title-->
<div id="s312" data-link-target="s312" data-id="section/312" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 93</h3><!--Section: section/313, type: body-->
<div id="s313" data-link-target="s313" data-id="section/313" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Each Chamber of the Parliament enjoys financial autonomy. Each President manages the credits which are allotted to him for the functioning of the Chamber.</p></div><!--Section: section/314, type: body-->
<div id="s314" data-link-target="s314" data-id="section/314" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President is responsible for this management before the Chamber; it can dismiss him by the absolute majority for incompetence in his management.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/315, type: title-->
<div id="s315" data-link-target="s315" data-id="section/315" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legrep">Replacement of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 94</h3><!--Section: section/316, type: body-->
<div id="s316" data-link-target="s316" data-id="section/316" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every elected member of the Parliament appointed to high functions is replaced by a substitute. The list of the high functions is determined by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/317, type: body-->
<div id="s317" data-link-target="s317" data-id="section/317" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If he ceases to exercise his functions at the latest before the end of the [first] half of the legislature, he can retake his seat; beyond this date, he may only retake it in case of vacancy of the seat by the death or resignation of the substitute.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/318, type: title-->
<div id="s318" data-link-target="s318" data-id="section/318" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="immunity">Immunity of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 95</h3><!--Section: section/319, type: body-->
<div id="s319" data-link-target="s319" data-id="section/319" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">No member of the Parliament may be prosecuted, investigated, arrested, detained or judged for reason of the opinions or votes emitted by him during the exercise or on the occasion of the exercise of his functions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/320, type: title-->
<div id="s320" data-link-target="s320" data-id="section/320" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="stdcom">Standing committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="immunity">Immunity of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 96</h3><!--Section: section/321, type: body-->
<div id="s321" data-link-target="s321" data-id="section/321" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Except in the case of flagrante delicto, any member of the Parliament may only be prosecuted or arrested in a penal or criminal matter with the authorization of at least one-third of the members of the Chamber of which he is a member during the sessions or of the Bureau of that Chamber when out of the sessions.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/322, type: title-->
<div id="s322" data-link-target="s322" data-id="section/322" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE VI. OF THE RESPECTIVE DOMAINS OF THE LAW AND OF REGULATION</h3><!--Section: section/323, type: title-->
<div id="s323" data-link-target="s323" data-id="section/323" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="orglaw">Organic laws</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="stdcom">Standing committees</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 97</h3><!--Section: section/324, type: body-->
<div id="s324" data-link-target="s324" data-id="section/324" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law is a deliberation, regularly promulgated[,] of the Parliament.</p></div><!--Section: section/325, type: body-->
<div id="s325" data-link-target="s325" data-id="section/325" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law to which the Constitution confers the organic character is a deliberation of the Parliament having for its object the organization or the functioning of the institutions. It is voted by the absolute majority and promulgated after declaration of its conformity with the Constitution by the Constitutional Council.</p></div><!--Section: section/326, type: body-->
<div id="s326" data-link-target="s326" data-id="section/326" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The initiative of the law belongs concurrently to the Deputies, to the Senators and to the Government. The drafts of texts emanating from the Deputies of from the Senators are called &quot;proposals of law&quot; and those emanating from the Government &quot;bills of law&quot;.</p></div><!--Section: section/327, type: body-->
<div id="s327" data-link-target="s327" data-id="section/327" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The proposals and bills of law are deliberated in the Council of Ministers before their deposit with the Bureau of each Chamber of the Parliament.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/328, type: title-->
<div id="s328" data-link-target="s328" data-id="section/328" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="stdcom">Standing committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="initiat">Legislative initiatives by citizens</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 98</h3><!--Section: section/329, type: body-->
<div id="s329" data-link-target="s329" data-id="section/329" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The people exercise the initiative of the laws by way of petition constituting a proposal[,] written and signed by at least fifteen thousand (15,000) persons having the right to vote under the conditions specified by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/330, type: body-->
<div id="s330" data-link-target="s330" data-id="section/330" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The petition is deposited with the Bureau of the National Assembly.</p></div><!--Section: section/331, type: body-->
<div id="s331" data-link-target="s331" data-id="section/331" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The right of amendment belongs to the Deputies, to the Senators and to the Government whatever the origin of the text may be.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/332, type: title-->
<div id="s332" data-link-target="s332" data-id="section/332" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdec">Head of government decree power</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 99</h3><!--Section: section/333, type: body-->
<div id="s333" data-link-target="s333" data-id="section/333" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The ordinance is an act signed by the President of Faso, after deliberation of the Council of Ministers, within the domains reserved to the law and in the cases specified in Articles 103, 107 and 119 of this Constitution. It enters into force on its publication.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/334, type: title-->
<div id="s334" data-link-target="s334" data-id="section/334" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdec">Head of government decree power</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosdec">Head of state decree power</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 100</h3><!--Section: section/335, type: body-->
<div id="s335" data-link-target="s335" data-id="section/335" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The simple decree is an act signed by the President of Faso or by the Prime Minister and countersigned by one or more competent members of the Government.</p></div><!--Section: section/336, type: body-->
<div id="s336" data-link-target="s336" data-id="section/336" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The decree in the Council of Ministers is an act signed by the President of Faso and by the Prime Minister after the opinion of the Council of Ministers: it is countersigned by one or more competent members of the Government.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/337, type: title-->
<div id="s337" data-link-target="s337" data-id="section/337" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 101</h3><!--Section: section/338, type: body-->
<div id="s338" data-link-target="s338" data-id="section/338" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes the rules concerning:</p><!--Section: section/339, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s339" data-link-target="s339" data-id="section/339">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="citizen">Requirements for birthright citizenship</span>
</div>citizenship, civic rights and the exercise of the public freedoms;<!--Section: section/341, type: body-->
<div id="s341" data-link-target="s341" data-id="section/341" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">constraints arising from the necessities of the National Defense;</p></div><!--Section: section/342, type: body-->
<div id="s342" data-link-target="s342" data-id="section/342" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="citizen">Requirements for birthright citizenship</span>
</div><p class="content">nationality, the state and capacity of persons, the matrimonial regimes;</p></div><!--Section: section/343, type: body-->
<div id="s343" data-link-target="s343" data-id="section/343" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="transfer">Right to transfer property</span>
</div><p class="content">inheritance and gifts;</p></div><!--Section: section/344, type: body-->
<div id="s344" data-link-target="s344" data-id="section/344" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the procedure according to which custom may be asserted and harmonized with the fundamental principles of the Constitution;</p></div><!--Section: section/345, type: body-->
<div id="s345" data-link-target="s345" data-id="section/345" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the promotion of gender;</p></div><!--Section: section/346, type: body-->
<div id="s346" data-link-target="s346" data-id="section/346" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the determination of crimes and misdemeanors, as well as the penalties which are applicable to them, the penal procedure, [and] amnesty;</p></div><!--Section: section/347, type: body-->
<div id="s347" data-link-target="s347" data-id="section/347" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the organization of judicial and administrative tribunals and the procedure before these jurisdictions, the status of the magistrates, [and] of the ministerial and auxiliary officers of justice;</p></div><!--Section: section/348, type: body-->
<div id="s348" data-link-target="s348" data-id="section/348" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the basis, the rate and the modalities of collecting taxes of all kinds;</p></div><!--Section: section/349, type: body-->
<div id="s349" data-link-target="s349" data-id="section/349" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the regime of the issuance of money;</p></div><!--Section: section/350, type: body-->
<div id="s350" data-link-target="s350" data-id="section/350" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the electoral regime of the National Assembly, of the Senate and of the local assemblies;</p></div><!--Section: section/351, type: body-->
<div id="s351" data-link-target="s351" data-id="section/351" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the nationalization of enterprises and the transfers of property of enterprises of the public sector to the private sector;</p></div><!--Section: section/352, type: body-->
<div id="s352" data-link-target="s352" data-id="section/352" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the creation of categories of public establishments;</p></div><!--Section: section/353, type: body-->
<div id="s353" data-link-target="s353" data-id="section/353" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>
</div><p class="content">the state of siege and the state of urgency.</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/354, type: body-->
<div id="s354" data-link-target="s354" data-id="section/354" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law determines the fundamental principles:</p><!--Section: section/355, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s355" data-link-target="s355" data-id="section/355">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="env">Protection of environment</span>
</div>of the protection and of the promotion of the environment;<!--Section: section/357, type: body-->
<div id="s357" data-link-target="s357" data-id="section/357" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="econplan">Economic plans</span>
</div><p class="content">of the drafting, of the execution and of the review of the national plans and programs of development;</p></div><!--Section: section/358, type: body-->
<div id="s358" data-link-target="s358" data-id="section/358" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="infoacc">Right to information</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="press">Freedom of press</span>
</div><p class="content">of the protection of the freedom of the press and of the access to information;</p></div><!--Section: section/359, type: body-->
<div id="s359" data-link-target="s359" data-id="section/359" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the general organization of the Administration;</p></div><!--Section: section/360, type: body-->
<div id="s360" data-link-target="s360" data-id="section/360" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the general status of the public function;</p></div><!--Section: section/361, type: body-->
<div id="s361" data-link-target="s361" data-id="section/361" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the organization of the national defense;</p></div><!--Section: section/362, type: body-->
<div id="s362" data-link-target="s362" data-id="section/362" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="science">Reference to science</span>
</div><p class="content">of education and of scientific research;</p></div><!--Section: section/363, type: body-->
<div id="s363" data-link-target="s363" data-id="section/363" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the integration of the national cultural values;</p></div><!--Section: section/364, type: body-->
<div id="s364" data-link-target="s364" data-id="section/364" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the regime of property, of the rights of real property and of civil and commercial obligations;</p></div><!--Section: section/365, type: body-->
<div id="s365" data-link-target="s365" data-id="section/365" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="provwork">Right to work</span>
</div><p class="content">of the right to work, of the syndical right, and of the social institutions;</p></div><!--Section: section/366, type: body-->
<div id="s366" data-link-target="s366" data-id="section/366" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the alienation and of the management of the domain of the State;</p></div><!--Section: section/367, type: body-->
<div id="s367" data-link-target="s367" data-id="section/367" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the penitentiary regime;</p></div><!--Section: section/368, type: body-->
<div id="s368" data-link-target="s368" data-id="section/368" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of insurance and of savings;</p></div><!--Section: section/369, type: body-->
<div id="s369" data-link-target="s369" data-id="section/369" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the organization of production;</p></div><!--Section: section/370, type: body-->
<div id="s370" data-link-target="s370" data-id="section/370" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">of the regime of transportation and communications;</p></div><!--Section: section/371, type: body-->
<div id="s371" data-link-target="s371" data-id="section/371" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="sub">Subsidiary unit government</span>
</div><p class="content">of the free administration of the territorial collectivities, of their competences and of their resources.</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div><!--Section: section/372, type: title-->
<div id="s372" data-link-target="s372" data-id="section/372" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 102</h3><!--Section: section/373, type: body-->
<div id="s373" data-link-target="s373" data-id="section/373" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law of finance determines, for each year, the resources and the obligations of the State. The bill of the law of finance must specify the receipts necessary for the integral coverage of expenses.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/374, type: title-->
<div id="s374" data-link-target="s374" data-id="section/374" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 103</h3><!--Section: section/375, type: body-->
<div id="s375" data-link-target="s375" data-id="section/375" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament votes the bill of the law of finance within the conditions provided for by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/376, type: body-->
<div id="s376" data-link-target="s376" data-id="section/376" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The National Assembly is referred to [the matter] of the bill of the law of finance at the opening of the second ordinary session.</p></div><!--Section: section/377, type: body-->
<div id="s377" data-link-target="s377" data-id="section/377" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The National Assembly decides [statue] first within a time of sixty days after the deposit of the bill and the Senate has at its disposal fifteen days counting from the date of reception to decide.</p></div><!--Section: section/378, type: body-->
<div id="s378" data-link-target="s378" data-id="section/378" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the Senate adopts a text identical to that of the National Assembly, the law is transmitted without delay to the President of Faso for promulgation.</p></div><!--Section: section/379, type: body-->
<div id="s379" data-link-target="s379" data-id="section/379" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the Senate has not decided within the time required or is in disagreement with the National Assembly, the bill is transmitted with urgency to the National Assembly which decides definitively.</p></div><!--Section: section/380, type: body-->
<div id="s380" data-link-target="s380" data-id="section/380" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The provisions of the bill can be put into force by ordinance if the Assembly has not decided at the latest on the date of the cloture of the session and only if the budgetary year is about to expire. In this case, the Government convokes an extraordinary session, in order to demand the ratification. If the budget is not voted at the end of the extraordinary session, it is definitively established by ordinance.</p></div><!--Section: section/381, type: body-->
<div id="s381" data-link-target="s381" data-id="section/381" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the bill of the law of finance has not been dealt with in a timely fashion to be voted and promulgated before the beginning of the fiscal year, the Prime Minister demands of urgency of the Assembly the authorization to restore the budget of the preceding year by provisional twelfths.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/382, type: title-->
<div id="s382" data-link-target="s382" data-id="section/382" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 104</h3><!--Section: section/383, type: body-->
<div id="s383" data-link-target="s383" data-id="section/383" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In the course of the execution of the budget, when the circumstances require it, the Government proposes to the Parliament, the adoption of rectifying laws of finance.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/384, type: title-->
<div id="s384" data-link-target="s384" data-id="section/384" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 105</h3><!--Section: section/385, type: body-->
<div id="s385" data-link-target="s385" data-id="section/385" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament regulates the accounts of the Nation, according to the modalities specified by the law of finance.</p></div><!--Section: section/386, type: body-->
<div id="s386" data-link-target="s386" data-id="section/386" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It is, to this effect, assisted by the Court of Accounts which is responsible for all inquiries and studies concerning the execution of the public receipts and expenses, or the management of the national treasury, of the territorial collectivities, of the administrations or institutions arising from the State or submitted to its control.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/387, type: title-->
<div id="s387" data-link-target="s387" data-id="section/387" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="war">Power to declare/approve war</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="em">Emergency provisions</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="comchief">Designation of commander in chief</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 106</h3><!--Section: section/388, type: body-->
<div id="s388" data-link-target="s388" data-id="section/388" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament meets of plain right in the case of [a] state of siege, if it is not in session. The state of siege can only be extended more than fifteen days with the authorization of the Parliament.</p></div><!--Section: section/389, type: body-->
<div id="s389" data-link-target="s389" data-id="section/389" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The declaration of war and the sending of military contingents or observers abroad are authorized by the Parliament.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/390, type: title-->
<div id="s390" data-link-target="s390" data-id="section/390" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdec">Head of government decree power</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 107</h3><!--Section: section/391, type: body-->
<div id="s391" data-link-target="s391" data-id="section/391" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Government can, for the execution of its programs, demand of the Parliament the authorization to take by ordinance, for a limited time period, measures which are normally of the domain of the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/392, type: body-->
<div id="s392" data-link-target="s392" data-id="section/392" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The ordinances are taken in the Council of Ministers after the opinion of the Constitutional Council. They enter into force on their publication, but become lapsed if the bill of law of ratification is not deposited with the National Assembly before the date established by the enabling law.</p></div><!--Section: section/393, type: body-->
<div id="s393" data-link-target="s393" data-id="section/393" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">On the expiration of the time period mentioned in the first paragraph of this Article, the ordinances may only be modified by the law in those of their provisions which are of the legislative domain.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/394, type: title-->
<div id="s394" data-link-target="s394" data-id="section/394" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 108</h3><!--Section: section/395, type: body-->
<div id="s395" data-link-target="s395" data-id="section/395" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The matters other than those corresponding to the domain of the law have a regulatory character.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/396, type: title-->
<div id="s396" data-link-target="s396" data-id="section/396" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE VII. OF THE RELATIONS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT AND THE PARLIAMENT</h3><!--Section: section/397, type: title-->
<div id="s397" data-link-target="s397" data-id="section/397" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogpow">Head of government powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="invexe">Legislative oversight of the executive</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 109</h3><!--Section: section/398, type: body-->
<div id="s398" data-link-target="s398" data-id="section/398" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister has access to the Parliament. He can give responsibility to a member of the Government of representation before the Parliament; that [member] can be assisted, in the course of the debates or in commission, by the members of the Government, [by] counselors or experts of his choice.</p></div><!--Section: section/399, type: body-->
<div id="s399" data-link-target="s399" data-id="section/399" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister presents directly to the Deputies the state of the Nation on the opening of the first session of the National Assembly.</p></div><!--Section: section/400, type: body-->
<div id="s400" data-link-target="s400" data-id="section/400" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">This presentation is followed by debate and does not give rise to any vote.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/401, type: title-->
<div id="s401" data-link-target="s401" data-id="section/401" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 110</h3><!--Section: section/402, type: body-->
<div id="s402" data-link-target="s402" data-id="section/402" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the Government have access to the Parliament, to its commissions and consultative organs. They can be assisted by counselors or experts.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/403, type: title-->
<div id="s403" data-link-target="s403" data-id="section/403" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="invexe">Legislative oversight of the executive</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 111</h3><!--Section: section/404, type: body-->
<div id="s404" data-link-target="s404" data-id="section/404" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">During the sessions, at least one sitting per week is reserved to the questions of the members of the Parliament and to the responses of the Government.</p></div><!--Section: section/405, type: body-->
<div id="s405" data-link-target="s405" data-id="section/405" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament can address to the Government questions on current events, written questions, [or] oral questions with or without debate.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/406, type: title-->
<div id="s406" data-link-target="s406" data-id="section/406" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="lhspleg">First chamber reserved policy areas</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="econplan">Economic plans</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uhspleg">Second chamber reserved policy areas</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="cabpow">Powers of cabinet</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legini">Initiation of general legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="divhouse">Division of labor between chambers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 112</h3><!--Section: section/407, type: body-->
<div id="s407" data-link-target="s407" data-id="section/407" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Government deposits the bills of law before the Parliament within the conditions provided for by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/408, type: body-->
<div id="s408" data-link-target="s408" data-id="section/408" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It presents and defends before it the governmental policy, the budget of the State, [and] the plans and programs of economic and social development of the Nation.</p></div><!--Section: section/409, type: body-->
<div id="s409" data-link-target="s409" data-id="section/409" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In accordance with the law, the Government participates in the debates concerning the orientation, the legitimacy, the merit and the effectiveness of the policy of the Government.</p></div><!--Section: section/410, type: body-->
<div id="s410" data-link-target="s410" data-id="section/410" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Every bill of law is examined successively in the two Chambers of the Parliament. The bills of law are, after their adoption by the National Assembly, transmitted to the Senate which decides within a time of twenty days counting from the date of reception, with exception made for the law of finance. In case of urgency declared by the Government, the time is reduced to five days.</p></div><!--Section: section/411, type: body-->
<div id="s411" data-link-target="s411" data-id="section/411" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the Senate adopts a text identical to that of the National Assembly, the law is transmitted without delay to the President of Faso for promulgation. In case of disagreement between the National Assembly and the Senate, or if the Senate has not decided within the time required, the National Assembly decides definitively.</p></div><!--Section: section/412, type: body-->
<div id="s412" data-link-target="s412" data-id="section/412" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, the bills of law having for [their] principal object the organization of the territorial collectivities and of the representative instances of the Burkinabe established outside of Burkina Faso are submitted first to the Senate.</p></div><!--Section: section/413, type: body-->
<div id="s413" data-link-target="s413" data-id="section/413" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In this case, if there is disagreement between the two Chambers, the Senate decides definitively.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/414, type: title-->
<div id="s414" data-link-target="s414" data-id="section/414" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="invexe">Legislative oversight of the executive</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 113</h3><!--Section: section/415, type: body-->
<div id="s415" data-link-target="s415" data-id="section/415" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Government is required to furnish to the Parliament all explanations which are demanded of it on its management and on its acts.</p></div><!--Section: section/416, type: body-->
<div id="s416" data-link-target="s416" data-id="section/416" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Parliament may constitute commissions of inquiry.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/417, type: title-->
<div id="s417" data-link-target="s417" data-id="section/417" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 114</h3><!--Section: section/418, type: body-->
<div id="s418" data-link-target="s418" data-id="section/418" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The reciprocal relations of the National Assembly and of the Government are expressed equally by:</p><!--Section: section/419, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s419" data-link-target="s419" data-id="section/419">the motion of censure;<!--Section: section/421, type: body-->
<div id="s421" data-link-target="s421" data-id="section/421" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the question of confidence;</p></div><!--Section: section/422, type: body-->
<div id="s422" data-link-target="s422" data-id="section/422" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the dissolution of the National Assembly;</p></div><!--Section: section/423, type: body-->
<div id="s423" data-link-target="s423" data-id="section/423" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the procedure of parliamentary discussion.</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div><!--Section: section/424, type: title-->
<div id="s424" data-link-target="s424" data-id="section/424" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdlim">Limits on removing head of government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 115</h3><!--Section: section/425, type: body-->
<div id="s425" data-link-target="s425" data-id="section/425" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The National Assembly can present a motion of censure with regard to the Government. The motion of censure is signed by at least one-third of the Deputies of the Assembly. To be adopted, it must be voted by an absolute majority of the members composing the Assembly. In case of rejection of the motion of censure, its signatories may not present another before the time period of one year.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/426, type: title-->
<div id="s426" data-link-target="s426" data-id="section/426" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 116</h3><!--Section: section/427, type: body-->
<div id="s427" data-link-target="s427" data-id="section/427" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister can, after deliberation of the Council of Ministers, engage before the National Assembly the responsibility of the Government on a program or on a declaration of general policy.</p></div><!--Section: section/428, type: body-->
<div id="s428" data-link-target="s428" data-id="section/428" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The confidence in the Government is refused if the text presented does not receive the absolute majority of the votes of the members composing the Assembly.</p></div><!--Section: section/429, type: body-->
<div id="s429" data-link-target="s429" data-id="section/429" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The vote on the question of confidence may not take place less than forty-eight hours after the deposit of the text.</p></div><!--Section: section/430, type: body-->
<div id="s430" data-link-target="s430" data-id="section/430" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Prime Minister can, after deliberation of the Council of Ministers, engage the responsibility of the Government before the Assembly on the adoption of a text. In this case, this text is considered adopted except if a motion of censure, deposited within the twenty-four hours which follow, is adopted in the conditions specified in the paragraphs above.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/431, type: title-->
<div id="s431" data-link-target="s431" data-id="section/431" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hogsucc">Head of government replacement</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hogdiss">Head of government removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 117</h3><!--Section: section/432, type: body-->
<div id="s432" data-link-target="s432" data-id="section/432" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the motion of censure is voted or confidence is refused, the President of Faso terminates, within a time period of eight days, the functions of the Prime Minster. He appoints a new Prime Minister according to the procedure specified in Article 46.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/433, type: title-->
<div id="s433" data-link-target="s433" data-id="section/433" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 118</h3><!--Section: section/434, type: body-->
<div id="s434" data-link-target="s434" data-id="section/434" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The agenda of each Chamber of the Parliament consists of the discussion of the popular petitions, of the bills deposited by the Government and of the proposals accepted by it.</p></div><!--Section: section/435, type: body-->
<div id="s435" data-link-target="s435" data-id="section/435" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Nevertheless, any proposal of law can be discussed two months after its submission to the Government without application of the preceding paragraph having been made, or of Articles 121 and 122 of this Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/436, type: body-->
<div id="s436" data-link-target="s436" data-id="section/436" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The inscription, by priority, in the agenda of the Chambers, of a bill or proposition of law or of a declaration of general policy, is of right if the President of Faso or of the Prime Minister makes the demand for it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/437, type: title-->
<div id="s437" data-link-target="s437" data-id="section/437" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 119</h3><!--Section: section/438, type: body-->
<div id="s438" data-link-target="s438" data-id="section/438" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In case of urgency declared by the Government, the Parliament must decide on the bills of law within a time period of fifteen days. This time period is extended to forty days for the law of finance. If at the expiration of the time period no vote has been taken, the bill of law is promulgated unchanged, on proposal of the Prime Minister by the President of Faso, in the form of an ordinance.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/439, type: title-->
<div id="s439" data-link-target="s439" data-id="section/439" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="balbudgt">Balanced budget</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="budget">Budget bills</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 120</h3><!--Section: section/440, type: body-->
<div id="s440" data-link-target="s440" data-id="section/440" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The proposals and amendments concerning the law of finance deposited by the members of the Parliament are irreceivable when their adoption would have as a consequence, either a diminution of public resources, or the creation or the increase of a public expense, unless they should be accompanied by a proposal for augmentation of receipts or of equivalent economies.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/441, type: title-->
<div id="s441" data-link-target="s441" data-id="section/441" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 121</h3><!--Section: section/442, type: body-->
<div id="s442" data-link-target="s442" data-id="section/442" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the Government demands it, the Chamber of the Parliament referred to [a matter] decides by a single vote on all or part of a text in discussion retaining in it only the amendments proposed or accepted by it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/443, type: title-->
<div id="s443" data-link-target="s443" data-id="section/443" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="commit">Legislative committees</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 122</h3><!--Section: section/444, type: body-->
<div id="s444" data-link-target="s444" data-id="section/444" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">When a Chamber of the Parliament has referred the examination of a draft of a text to a commission, the Government can, after the opening of debates[,] oppose the examination of any amendment which has not been preliminarily submitted to this commission.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/445, type: title-->
<div id="s445" data-link-target="s445" data-id="section/445" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 123</h3><!--Section: section/446, type: body-->
<div id="s446" data-link-target="s446" data-id="section/446" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The proposals and amendments which are not of the domain of the law are irreceivable. The irreceivability is decided by the President of the Chamber referred to [the matter].</p></div><!--Section: section/447, type: body-->
<div id="s447" data-link-target="s447" data-id="section/447" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In case of dispute, the Constitutional Council, on referral of the Prime Minister or of the President of the Chamber referred to [the matter], decides with a time period of eight days.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/448, type: title-->
<div id="s448" data-link-target="s448" data-id="section/448" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE VIII. OF THE JUDICIAL POWER</h3><!--Section: section/449, type: title-->
<div id="s449" data-link-target="s449" data-id="section/449" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 124</h3><!--Section: section/450, type: body-->
<div id="s450" data-link-target="s450" data-id="section/450" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Judicial Power is confided in the judges; it is exercised on all the territory of Burkina Faso by the jurisdictions of the judicial order and of the administrative order determined by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/451, type: title-->
<div id="s451" data-link-target="s451" data-id="section/451" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 125</h3><!--Section: section/452, type: body-->
<div id="s452" data-link-target="s452" data-id="section/452" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Judicial Power is the guardian of the individual and collective liberties.</p></div><!--Section: section/453, type: body-->
<div id="s453" data-link-target="s453" data-id="section/453" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It sees to the respect for the rights and freedoms defined in this Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/454, type: title-->
<div id="s454" data-link-target="s454" data-id="section/454" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="levjud">Structure of the courts</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 126</h3><!--Section: section/455, type: body-->
<div id="s455" data-link-target="s455" data-id="section/455" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The jurisdictions of the judicial order and of the administrative order of Burkina Faso are:</p><!--Section: section/456, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s456" data-link-target="s456" data-id="section/456">the Court of Cassation;<!--Section: section/458, type: body-->
<div id="s458" data-link-target="s458" data-id="section/458" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts1">Establishment of administrative courts</span>
</div><p class="content">the Council of State;</p></div><!--Section: section/459, type: body-->
<div id="s459" data-link-target="s459" data-id="section/459" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the Court of Accounts;</p></div><!--Section: section/460, type: body-->
<div id="s460" data-link-target="s460" data-id="section/460" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the Tribunal of Conflicts;</p></div><!--Section: section/461, type: body-->
<div id="s461" data-link-target="s461" data-id="section/461" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the courts and the tribunals instituted by the law;</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/462, type: body-->
<div id="s462" data-link-target="s462" data-id="section/462" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">These jurisdictions apply the law in force.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/463, type: title-->
<div id="s463" data-link-target="s463" data-id="section/463" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hocsel">Supreme court selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="ordsel">Ordinary court selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts5">Courts for judging public officials</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="levjud">Structure of the courts</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts2">Establishment of constitutional court</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts1">Establishment of administrative courts</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hocres">Eligibility for supreme court judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="suppow">Supreme court powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 127</h3><!--Section: section/464, type: body-->
<div id="s464" data-link-target="s464" data-id="section/464" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Court of Cassation is the superior jurisdiction of the judicial order.</p></div><!--Section: section/465, type: body-->
<div id="s465" data-link-target="s465" data-id="section/465" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Council of State is the superior jurisdiction of the administrative order.</p></div><!--Section: section/466, type: body-->
<div id="s466" data-link-target="s466" data-id="section/466" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Court of Accounts is the superior jurisdiction of control of the public finances.</p></div><!--Section: section/467, type: body-->
<div id="s467" data-link-target="s467" data-id="section/467" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Tribunal of Conflicts is the jurisdiction of regulation of the conflicts of competence between the jurisdictions.</p></div><!--Section: section/468, type: body-->
<div id="s468" data-link-target="s468" data-id="section/468" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the composition, the organization, the attributions, [and] the functioning of these jurisdictions, as well as the procedure applicable before them.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/469, type: title-->
<div id="s469" data-link-target="s469" data-id="section/469" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="adres">Eligibility for administrative  judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="ordres">Eligibility for ordinary court judges</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 128</h3><!--Section: section/470, type: body-->
<div id="s470" data-link-target="s470" data-id="section/470" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes the seat, the jurisdiction, the competence and the composition of courts and of the tribunals.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/471, type: title-->
<div id="s471" data-link-target="s471" data-id="section/471" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judind">Judicial independence</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 129</h3><!--Section: section/472, type: body-->
<div id="s472" data-link-target="s472" data-id="section/472" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The judicial power is independent.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/473, type: title-->
<div id="s473" data-link-target="s473" data-id="section/473" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="ordterm">Ordinary court term length</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hocterm">Supreme court term length</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 130</h3><!--Section: section/474, type: body-->
<div id="s474" data-link-target="s474" data-id="section/474" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The presiding magistrates are only submitted[,] in the exercise of their functions[,] to the authority of the law. They are not removable.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/475, type: title-->
<div id="s475" data-link-target="s475" data-id="section/475" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 131</h3><!--Section: section/476, type: body-->
<div id="s476" data-link-target="s476" data-id="section/476" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is the guarantor of the independence of the judicial power.</p></div><!--Section: section/477, type: body-->
<div id="s477" data-link-target="s477" data-id="section/477" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">He is assisted by the Superior Council of the Magistrature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/478, type: title-->
<div id="s478" data-link-target="s478" data-id="section/478" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 132</h3><!--Section: section/479, type: body-->
<div id="s479" data-link-target="s479" data-id="section/479" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso is the President of the Superior Council of the Magistrature.</p></div><!--Section: section/480, type: body-->
<div id="s480" data-link-target="s480" data-id="section/480" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Guardian of the Scales, the Minister of Justice, is the first vice president and the first President of the Court of Cassation is the second vice president.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/481, type: title-->
<div id="s481" data-link-target="s481" data-id="section/481" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 133</h3><!--Section: section/482, type: body-->
<div id="s482" data-link-target="s482" data-id="section/482" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Superior Council of the Magistrature gives its opinion on any question concerning the independence of the magistrature and on the exercise of the right of pardon.</p></div><!--Section: section/483, type: body-->
<div id="s483" data-link-target="s483" data-id="section/483" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the organization, the composition, the attributions and the functioning of the Superior Council of the Magistrature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/484, type: title-->
<div id="s484" data-link-target="s484" data-id="section/484" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="levjud">Structure of the courts</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="ordsel">Ordinary court selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="jc">Establishment of judicial council</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hocsel">Supreme court selection</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 134</h3><!--Section: section/485, type: body-->
<div id="s485" data-link-target="s485" data-id="section/485" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Superior Council of the Magistrature makes proposals on the appointments and the assignments of the presiding magistrates of the Court of Cassation, of the Council of State[,] and of the Court of Accounts and on those of the first presidents of the courts of appeal.</p></div><!--Section: section/486, type: body-->
<div id="s486" data-link-target="s486" data-id="section/486" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It gives its opinion on the proposals of the Minister of Justice, concerning the appointments of other presiding magistrates.</p></div><!--Section: section/487, type: body-->
<div id="s487" data-link-target="s487" data-id="section/487" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The prosecuting magistrates are appointed and assigned on proposal of the Minister of Justice.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/488, type: title-->
<div id="s488" data-link-target="s488" data-id="section/488" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 135</h3><!--Section: section/489, type: body-->
<div id="s489" data-link-target="s489" data-id="section/489" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the status of the magistrature with respect for the principles contained in this Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/490, type: body-->
<div id="s490" data-link-target="s490" data-id="section/490" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It provides for and organizes the guarantees and the independence of the magistrature.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/491, type: title-->
<div id="s491" data-link-target="s491" data-id="section/491" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="pubtri">Right to public trial</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 136</h3><!--Section: section/492, type: body-->
<div id="s492" data-link-target="s492" data-id="section/492" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Hearings in all the courts and in all the tribunals are public. The closed hearing is only allowed in the cases defined by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/493, type: body-->
<div id="s493" data-link-target="s493" data-id="section/493" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The decisions of the jurisdictions are substantiated, except in the cases where the law provides otherwise for it.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/494, type: title-->
<div id="s494" data-link-target="s494" data-id="section/494" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE IX. OF THE HIGH COURT OF JUSTICE</h3><!--Section: section/495, type: title-->
<div id="s495" data-link-target="s495" data-id="section/495" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts5">Courts for judging public officials</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 137</h3><!--Section: section/496, type: body-->
<div id="s496" data-link-target="s496" data-id="section/496" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A High Court of Justice is instituted. The High Court of Justice is composed of Deputies that the National Assembly elects after each general renewal, as well as the magistrates designated by the President of the Court of Cassation. It elects its President from among its members.</p></div><!--Section: section/497, type: body-->
<div id="s497" data-link-target="s497" data-id="section/497" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes its composition, the rules of its functioning and the procedure applicable before it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/498, type: title-->
<div id="s498" data-link-target="s498" data-id="section/498" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts5">Courts for judging public officials</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 138</h3><!--Section: section/499, type: body-->
<div id="s499" data-link-target="s499" data-id="section/499" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The High Court of Justice is competent to take cognizance of the acts committed by the President of Faso in the exercise of his functions and constituting high treason, of infringing the Constitution or of misappropriation of public funds.</p></div><!--Section: section/500, type: body-->
<div id="s500" data-link-target="s500" data-id="section/500" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The High Court of Justice is equally competent to judge the members of Government for reason of acts qualified as crimes or misdemeanors committed in the exercise or on the occasion of the exercise of their functions. In all other cases, they remain justiciable by the jurisdictions of common law and of the other jurisdictions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/501, type: title-->
<div id="s501" data-link-target="s501" data-id="section/501" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 139</h3><!--Section: section/502, type: body-->
<div id="s502" data-link-target="s502" data-id="section/502" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The impeachment of the President of Faso is voted by a majority of four-fifths of the votes of the Deputies composing the Assembly. That of the members of the Government is voted by a majority of two-thirds of the votes of the Deputies composing the Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/503, type: title-->
<div id="s503" data-link-target="s503" data-id="section/503" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosdiss">Head of state removal</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 140</h3><!--Section: section/504, type: body-->
<div id="s504" data-link-target="s504" data-id="section/504" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The High Court of Justice is constrained by the definition of crimes and misdemeanors and by the determination of the resultant punishments of the criminal laws in force at the time when the acts were committed.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/505, type: title-->
<div id="s505" data-link-target="s505" data-id="section/505" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE X. OF THE ECONOMIC AND SOCIAL COUNCIL AND OF THE ORGANS OF CONTROL</h3><!--Section: section/506, type: title-->
<div id="s506" data-link-target="s506" data-id="section/506" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="hosstaff">Advisory bodies to the head of state</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 141</h3><!--Section: section/507, type: body-->
<div id="s507" data-link-target="s507" data-id="section/507" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A consultative organ denominated the Economic and Social Council (CES), is instituted.</p></div><!--Section: section/508, type: body-->
<div id="s508" data-link-target="s508" data-id="section/508" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Economic and Social Council is charged to give its opinion on the questions of economic, social or cultural character brought to its attention by the President of Faso or the Government.</p></div><!--Section: section/509, type: body-->
<div id="s509" data-link-target="s509" data-id="section/509" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It may be consulted on any draft of [a] plan or of [a] program of economic, social or cultural character.</p></div><!--Section: section/510, type: body-->
<div id="s510" data-link-target="s510" data-id="section/510" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Economic and Social Council can equally proceed to an analysis of any problem of economic and social development. It submits its conclusion to the President of Faso or to the Government.</p></div><!--Section: section/511, type: body-->
<div id="s511" data-link-target="s511" data-id="section/511" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Economic and Social Council may designate one of its members[,] on the demand of the President of Faso or of the Government, to present before these organs, the opinion of the Council on the questions which have been submitted to it.</p></div><!--Section: section/512, type: body-->
<div id="s512" data-link-target="s512" data-id="section/512" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the composition, the organization and the functioning of the Economic and Social Council.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/513, type: title-->
<div id="s513" data-link-target="s513" data-id="section/513" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 142</h3><!--Section: section/514, type: body-->
<div id="s514" data-link-target="s514" data-id="section/514" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The organs of control are created by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/515, type: body-->
<div id="s515" data-link-target="s515" data-id="section/515" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Their competence concerns question of economic, social and cultural character of national interest.</p></div><!--Section: section/516, type: body-->
<div id="s516" data-link-target="s516" data-id="section/516" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The composition, the attributions and the functioning of these organs of control are established by the law.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/517, type: title-->
<div id="s517" data-link-target="s517" data-id="section/517" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XI. OF THE TERRITORIAL COLLECTIVITIES</h3><!--Section: section/518, type: title-->
<div id="s518" data-link-target="s518" data-id="section/518" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="sub">Subsidiary unit government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 143</h3><!--Section: section/519, type: body-->
<div id="s519" data-link-target="s519" data-id="section/519" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Burkina Faso is organized in territorial collectivities.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/520, type: title-->
<div id="s520" data-link-target="s520" data-id="section/520" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="sub">Subsidiary unit government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 144</h3><!--Section: section/521, type: body-->
<div id="s521" data-link-target="s521" data-id="section/521" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The creation, the elimination, and the division of territorial collectivities is the resort of the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/522, type: title-->
<div id="s522" data-link-target="s522" data-id="section/522" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="sub">Subsidiary unit government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 145</h3><!--Section: section/523, type: body-->
<div id="s523" data-link-target="s523" data-id="section/523" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law organizes the democratic participation of the populations in the free administration of the territorial collectivities.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/524, type: title-->
<div id="s524" data-link-target="s524" data-id="section/524" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XII. OF AFRICAN UNITY</h3><!--Section: section/525, type: title-->
<div id="s525" data-link-target="s525" data-id="section/525" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="region">Regional group(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 146</h3><!--Section: section/526, type: body-->
<div id="s526" data-link-target="s526" data-id="section/526" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Burkina Faso may conclude with any African State agreements of association or of community implying a total or partial abandonment of sovereignty.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/527, type: title-->
<div id="s527" data-link-target="s527" data-id="section/527" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="region">Regional group(s)</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 147</h3><!--Section: section/528, type: body-->
<div id="s528" data-link-target="s528" data-id="section/528" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The agreements consecrating the entry of Burkina Faso into a Confederation, a Federation or a Union of African States are submitted to the approval of the People by referendum.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/529, type: title-->
<div id="s529" data-link-target="s529" data-id="section/529" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XIII. OF TREATIES AND INTERNATIONAL AGREEMENTS</h3><!--Section: section/530, type: title-->
<div id="s530" data-link-target="s530" data-id="section/530" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="intlaw">International law</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 148</h3><!--Section: section/531, type: body-->
<div id="s531" data-link-target="s531" data-id="section/531" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso negotiates, signs and ratifies the international treaties and agreements.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/532, type: title-->
<div id="s532" data-link-target="s532" data-id="section/532" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="treatcon">Legal status of treaties</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 149</h3><!--Section: section/533, type: body-->
<div id="s533" data-link-target="s533" data-id="section/533" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Peace treaties, the treaties of commerce, the treaties which engage the finances of the State, those which modify the provisions of legislative nature, [and] those that concern the state of persons, can only be ratified or approved by virtue of law.</p></div><!--Section: section/534, type: body-->
<div id="s534" data-link-target="s534" data-id="section/534" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">They can only take effect after having been ratified or approved.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/535, type: title-->
<div id="s535" data-link-target="s535" data-id="section/535" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="treatcon">Legal status of treaties</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 150</h3><!--Section: section/536, type: body-->
<div id="s536" data-link-target="s536" data-id="section/536" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If the Constitutional Council, referred to [the matter] conforming to Article 157, has declared that an international commitment contains a provision contrary to the Constitution, the authorization to ratify it or to approve it can only take place after the revision of the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/537, type: title-->
<div id="s537" data-link-target="s537" data-id="section/537" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="treatcon">Legal status of treaties</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="intlaw">International law</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 151</h3><!--Section: section/538, type: body-->
<div id="s538" data-link-target="s538" data-id="section/538" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The treaties and agreements regularly ratified or approved have, on their publication, an authority superior to that of the laws, under reserve, for each agreement or treaty, of its application by the other party.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/539, type: title-->
<div id="s539" data-link-target="s539" data-id="section/539" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="judcrts2">Establishment of constitutional court</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XIV. OF THE CONSTITUTIONAL COUNCIL</h3><!--Section: section/540, type: title-->
<div id="s540" data-link-target="s540" data-id="section/540" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conpow">Constitutional court powers</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 152</h3><!--Section: section/541, type: body-->
<div id="s541" data-link-target="s541" data-id="section/541" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council is the institution competent in constitutional and electoral matters. It is charged to decide on the constitutionality of the laws, of the ordinances as well as the conformity of the international treaties and agreements with the Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/542, type: body-->
<div id="s542" data-link-target="s542" data-id="section/542" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">It interprets the provisions of the Constitution. It controls the regularity, the transparency and the sincerity of the referendum, of the presidential elections, legislative [elections] and is the judge of electoral disputes. It proclaims the definitive results of the referendum, [and] of the presidential and legislative elections.</p></div><!--Section: section/543, type: body-->
<div id="s543" data-link-target="s543" data-id="section/543" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The control of the regularity and of the transparency of local elections corresponds to the competence of the administrative tribunals. The proclamation of the definitive results of these elections corresponds to the competence of the Council of State.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/544, type: title-->
<div id="s544" data-link-target="s544" data-id="section/544" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conterm">Constitutional court term length</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conres">Eligibility for const court judges</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="conlim">Constitutional court term limits</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="consel">Constitutional court selection</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="profleg">Outside professions of legislators</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 153</h3><!--Section: section/545, type: body-->
<div id="s545" data-link-target="s545" data-id="section/545" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council consists of:</p><!--Section: section/546, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s546" data-link-target="s546" data-id="section/546">the former Heads of State of Burkina Faso;<!--Section: section/548, type: body-->
<div id="s548" data-link-target="s548" data-id="section/548" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">three (3) magistrates appointed by the President of Faso on proposal of the Minister of Justice;</p></div><!--Section: section/549, type: body-->
<div id="s549" data-link-target="s549" data-id="section/549" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">three (3) persons of distinction appointed by the President of Faso having at least one jurist;</p></div><!--Section: section/550, type: body-->
<div id="s550" data-link-target="s550" data-id="section/550" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">three (3) persons of distinction appointed by the President of the National Assembly having at least one jurist;</p></div><!--Section: section/551, type: body-->
<div id="s551" data-link-target="s551" data-id="section/551" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">[and] three (3) persons of distinction appointed by the President of the Senate having at least one jurist.</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/552, type: body-->
<div id="s552" data-link-target="s552" data-id="section/552" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The members of the Constitutional Council are appointed for a sole mandate of nine (9) years. They elect from among themselves the President of the Constitutional Council.</p></div><!--Section: section/553, type: body-->
<div id="s553" data-link-target="s553" data-id="section/553" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">With the exception of the former Heads of State, the members of the Constitutional Council are renewable by thirds (1/3) every three years within the conditions established by the law.</p></div><!--Section: section/554, type: body-->
<div id="s554" data-link-target="s554" data-id="section/554" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The functions of member of the Constitutional Council are incompatible with those of a member of the Government or of the Parliament.</p></div><!--Section: section/555, type: body-->
<div id="s555" data-link-target="s555" data-id="section/555" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The other incompatibilities are established by the law.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/556, type: title-->
<div id="s556" data-link-target="s556" data-id="section/556" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="conpow">Constitutional court powers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 154</h3><!--Section: section/557, type: body-->
<div id="s557" data-link-target="s557" data-id="section/557" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council sees to the regularity of the presidential elections. It examines the complaints and proclaims the results of the ballot.</p></div><!--Section: section/558, type: body-->
<div id="s558" data-link-target="s558" data-id="section/558" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council decides, in case of dispute, on the regularity of the election or of the appointment of the members of the Parliament.</p></div><!--Section: section/559, type: body-->
<div id="s559" data-link-target="s559" data-id="section/559" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">In electoral matters, the Constitutional Council can be referred to [a matter] by any interested candidate.</p></div><!--Section: section/560, type: body-->
<div id="s560" data-link-target="s560" data-id="section/560" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council sees to the regularity of the operations of the referendum and proclaims the results of it.</p></div><!--Section: section/561, type: body-->
<div id="s561" data-link-target="s561" data-id="section/561" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council sees to respect for the procedure of revision of the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/562, type: title-->
<div id="s562" data-link-target="s562" data-id="section/562" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="treat">Treaty ratification</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="orglaw">Organic laws</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 155</h3><!--Section: section/563, type: body-->
<div id="s563" data-link-target="s563" data-id="section/563" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The organic laws and the regulations of the Chambers of the Parliament, before their promulgation or their entry into application[,] must be submitted to the Constitutional Council.</p></div><!--Section: section/564, type: body-->
<div id="s564" data-link-target="s564" data-id="section/564" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">To the same ends, the ordinary laws and the treaties submitted to the procedure of ratification, may be deferred to the Constitutional Council, before their  promulgation.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/565, type: title-->
<div id="s565" data-link-target="s565" data-id="section/565" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="partunco">Regulation of political parties</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 156</h3><!--Section: section/566, type: body-->
<div id="s566" data-link-target="s566" data-id="section/566" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council is also charged with the control of respect[,] by the political parties, for the provisions of Article 13 paragraph 5 of this Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/567, type: title-->
<div id="s567" data-link-target="s567" data-id="section/567" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="interp">Constitutional interpretation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 157</h3><!--Section: section/568, type: body-->
<div id="s568" data-link-target="s568" data-id="section/568" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council is referred to [a matter] by:</p><!--Section: section/569, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s569" data-link-target="s569" data-id="section/569">the President of Faso;<!--Section: section/571, type: body-->
<div id="s571" data-link-target="s571" data-id="section/571" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the Prime Minister;</p></div><!--Section: section/572, type: body-->
<div id="s572" data-link-target="s572" data-id="section/572" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the President of the Senate;</p></div><!--Section: section/573, type: body-->
<div id="s573" data-link-target="s573" data-id="section/573" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the President of the National Assembly;</p></div><!--Section: section/574, type: body-->
<div id="s574" data-link-target="s574" data-id="section/574" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">one-tenth (1/10) at least of the members of the National Assembly.</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/575, type: body-->
<div id="s575" data-link-target="s575" data-id="section/575" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">If, on the occasion of an instance in course before a jurisdiction, it is held that a legislative provision infringes the rights and freedoms that the Constitution guarantees, the Constitutional Council can be referred to [the matter] of this question on referral of the Council of State or of the Court of Cassation. The Constitutional Council decides within a time period determined by the law. An organic law determines the conditions of application of this provision.</p></div><!--Section: section/576, type: body-->
<div id="s576" data-link-target="s576" data-id="section/576" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Constitutional Council can refer itself to any questions relative to its competence, if it judges it necessary.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/577, type: title-->
<div id="s577" data-link-target="s577" data-id="section/577" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 158</h3><!--Section: section/578, type: body-->
<div id="s578" data-link-target="s578" data-id="section/578" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The referral of the Constitutional Council to [a matter] suspends the time period of the promulgation of the texts which are deferred to it.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/579, type: title-->
<div id="s579" data-link-target="s579" data-id="section/579" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="uncon">Constitutionality of legislation</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 159</h3><!--Section: section/580, type: body-->
<div id="s580" data-link-target="s580" data-id="section/580" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A provision declared unconstitutional may not be promulgated or implemented.</p></div><!--Section: section/581, type: body-->
<div id="s581" data-link-target="s581" data-id="section/581" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The decisions of the Constitutional Council are not susceptible to any recourse. They impose themselves on the public powers and on all the administrative and jurisdictional authorities.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/582, type: title-->
<div id="s582" data-link-target="s582" data-id="section/582" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 160</h3><!--Section: section/583, type: body-->
<div id="s583" data-link-target="s583" data-id="section/583" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the organization and the functioning of the Constitutional Council and determines the procedure applicable before it.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/584, type: title-->
<div id="s584" data-link-target="s584" data-id="section/584" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XIVbis. OF THE MEDIATOR OF FASO</h3><!--Section: section/585, type: title-->
<div id="s585" data-link-target="s585" data-id="section/585" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="ombuds">Ombudsman</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 160.1</h3><!--Section: section/586, type: body-->
<div id="s586" data-link-target="s586" data-id="section/586" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A gratuitous intercessory organ between the public administration and the citizens denominated the Mediator of Faso[,] is instituted.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/587, type: title-->
<div id="s587" data-link-target="s587" data-id="section/587" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="ombuds">Ombudsman</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 160.2</h3><!--Section: section/588, type: body-->
<div id="s588" data-link-target="s588" data-id="section/588" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the attributions, the organization and the functioning of the Mediator of Faso.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/589, type: title-->
<div id="s589" data-link-target="s589" data-id="section/589" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XIVter. OF THE SUPERIOR COUNCIL OF COMMUNICATION</h3><!--Section: section/590, type: title-->
<div id="s590" data-link-target="s590" data-id="section/590" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="medcom">Media commission</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 160.3</h3><!--Section: section/591, type: body-->
<div id="s591" data-link-target="s591" data-id="section/591" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An independent administrative authority of regulation of communication to the public denominated [the] Superior Council of Communication[,] abbreviated (CSC), is instituted.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/592, type: title-->
<div id="s592" data-link-target="s592" data-id="section/592" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="medcom">Media commission</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 160.4</h3><!--Section: section/593, type: body-->
<div id="s593" data-link-target="s593" data-id="section/593" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">An organic law establishes the attributions, the composition, the organization and the functioning of the Superior Council of Communication.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/594, type: title-->
<div id="s594" data-link-target="s594" data-id="section/594" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XV. OF REVISION</h3><!--Section: section/595, type: title-->
<div id="s595" data-link-target="s595" data-id="section/595" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 161</h3><!--Section: section/596, type: body-->
<div id="s596" data-link-target="s596" data-id="section/596" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The initiative of the revision of the Constitution belongs concurrently:</p><!--Section: section/597, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s597" data-link-target="s597" data-id="section/597">to the President of Faso;<!--Section: section/599, type: body-->
<div id="s599" data-link-target="s599" data-id="section/599" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">to the members of the Parliament by the majority of each of the Chambers;</p></div><!--Section: section/600, type: body-->
<div id="s600" data-link-target="s600" data-id="section/600" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">to the people when a fraction of at least thirty thousand (30,000) persons having the right to vote, introduces before the National Assembly a petition constituting a proposal, written and signed.</p></div>
</li></ul></div>
</div><!--Section: section/601, type: title-->
<div id="s601" data-link-target="s601" data-id="section/601" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 162</h3><!--Section: section/602, type: body-->
<div id="s602" data-link-target="s602" data-id="section/602" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The law establishes the conditions of the implementation of the procedure of revision.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/603, type: title-->
<div id="s603" data-link-target="s603" data-id="section/603" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 163</h3><!--Section: section/604, type: body-->
<div id="s604" data-link-target="s604" data-id="section/604" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The bill of revision is, in every case, submitted preliminarily to the evaluation of the Parliament.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/605, type: title-->
<div id="s605" data-link-target="s605" data-id="section/605" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="legjoint">Joint meetings of legislative chambers</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="referen">Referenda</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="stdcom">Standing committees</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 164</h3><!--Section: section/606, type: body-->
<div id="s606" data-link-target="s606" data-id="section/606" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The bill of the text is then submitted to referendum. It is considered to have been adopted when it has obtained the majority of the suffrage expressed.</p></div><!--Section: section/607, type: body-->
<div id="s607" data-link-target="s607" data-id="section/607" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The President of Faso then proceeds with its promulgation in the conditions established by Article 48 of this Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/608, type: body-->
<div id="s608" data-link-target="s608" data-id="section/608" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">However, the bill of revision is adopted without recourse to referendum if it is approved by a majority of three-quarters (3/4) of the members of the Parliament convoked in Congress by the President of Faso. The Bureau of the Congress is that of the National Assembly.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/609, type: title-->
<div id="s609" data-link-target="s609" data-id="section/609" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="unamend">Unamendable provisions</span>, <span class="topic" data-topic="amend">Constitution amendment procedure</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 165</h3><!--Section: section/610, type: body-->
<div id="s610" data-link-target="s610" data-id="section/610" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">No bill or proposal of revision of the Constitution is receivable when it effects:</p><!--Section: section/611, type: list-->
<ul><li id="s611" data-link-target="s611" data-id="section/611">the republican nature and form of the State;<!--Section: section/613, type: body-->
<div id="s613" data-link-target="s613" data-id="section/613" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the multiparty system;</p></div><!--Section: section/614, type: body-->
<div id="s614" data-link-target="s614" data-id="section/614" class="section article-list level2 article-body" style="display: list-item; list-style-type: disc;"><p class="content">the integrity of the national territory.</p></div>
</li></ul></div><!--Section: section/615, type: body-->
<div id="s615" data-link-target="s615" data-id="section/615" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">No procedure of revision may be initiated or pursued when it infringes upon the integrity of the territory.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/616, type: title-->
<div id="s616" data-link-target="s616" data-id="section/616" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XVI. FINAL PROVISIONS</h3><!--Section: section/617, type: title-->
<div id="s617" data-link-target="s617" data-id="section/617" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 166</h3><!--Section: section/618, type: body-->
<div id="s618" data-link-target="s618" data-id="section/618" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Treason against the Fatherland and infringement the Constitution constitute the most grave crimes committed against the people.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/619, type: title-->
<div id="s619" data-link-target="s619" data-id="section/619" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="overthrw">Right to overthrow government</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 167</h3><!--Section: section/620, type: body-->
<div id="s620" data-link-target="s620" data-id="section/620" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The source of all legitimacy follows from this Constitution.</p></div><!--Section: section/621, type: body-->
<div id="s621" data-link-target="s621" data-id="section/621" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">All power which does not derive its source from this Constitution, notably that resulting from a coup d&#x27;etat or from a putsch[,] is illegal. In this case, the right to civil disobedience is recognized to all citizens.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/622, type: title-->
<div id="s622" data-link-target="s622" data-id="section/622" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 168</h3><!--Section: section/623, type: body-->
<div id="s623" data-link-target="s623" data-id="section/623" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Burkinabe people proscribe any idea of personal power.</p></div><!--Section: section/624, type: body-->
<div id="s624" data-link-target="s624" data-id="section/624" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">They proscribe equally all oppression of a part of the people by another.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/625, type: title-->
<div id="s625" data-link-target="s625" data-id="section/625" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 168.1</h3><!--Section: section/626, type: body-->
<div id="s626" data-link-target="s626" data-id="section/626" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">A full [pleine] and entire amnesty is accorded to the Heads of State of Burkina Faso for the period running from 1960 to the date of adoption of these provisions.</p></div>
</div>
</div><!--Section: section/627, type: title-->
<div id="s627" data-link-target="s627" data-id="section/627" class="section article-list level0 article-title">
<div class="section-topic">
<span class="topic" data-topic="tranprov">Transitional provisions</span>
</div>
<h3 class="depth-0">TITLE XVI. TRANSITORY PROVISIONS</h3><!--Section: section/628, type: title-->
<div id="s628" data-link-target="s628" data-id="section/628" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 169</h3><!--Section: section/629, type: body-->
<div id="s629" data-link-target="s629" data-id="section/629" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The promulgation of the Constitution must intervene in the twenty-one days following its adoption by referendum.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/630, type: title-->
<div id="s630" data-link-target="s630" data-id="section/630" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 170</h3><!--Section: section/631, type: body-->
<div id="s631" data-link-target="s631" data-id="section/631" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The Head of State and the Government are enabled to take the measures necessary to establish the Institutions.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/632, type: title-->
<div id="s632" data-link-target="s632" data-id="section/632" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 171</h3><!--Section: section/633, type: body-->
<div id="s633" data-link-target="s633" data-id="section/633" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The presidential and legislative elections take place within the twelve (12) months which follow the adoption of the Constitution.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/634, type: title-->
<div id="s634" data-link-target="s634" data-id="section/634" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 172</h3><!--Section: section/635, type: body-->
<div id="s635" data-link-target="s635" data-id="section/635" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">Until the Institutions are established, the Head of State and the Government continue to act and take the measures necessary for the functioning of the public powers, for the life of the Nation, for the protection of citizens and the safeguarding of the freedoms.</p></div>
</div><!--Section: section/636, type: title-->
<div id="s636" data-link-target="s636" data-id="section/636" class="section article-list level1 article-title">
<h3 class="depth-1">Article 173</h3><!--Section: section/637, type: body-->
<div id="s637" data-link-target="s637" data-id="section/637" class="section article-list level2 article-body"><p class="content">The legislation in force remains applicable insofar as it is not contrary to this Constitution, until the intervention of new texts.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

  </div>
</div>

